Title: Turnigy nano-tech 4400mah 4S 65~130C Lipo Pack w/XT-90
Description: More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. Utilising an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and a higher discharge rates than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) batteries.For those that love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves and excellent performance. For pilots it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!Lithium Polymer batteries are used in many RC hobby industries. Over the last few years, Lipo batteries have become the most popular battery choice for anyone looking for a longer run time and higher power.Lipo batteries weigh less and can be made into almost any size or shape. Lipo batteries have higher capacities, hold more power and have a higher discharge rate, meaning they pack more punch. For safe use and storage of Lipo batteries, you need to follow the rules and treat the batteries with the respect they deserve.Spec.Capacity:4400mAhVoltage:4S1P / 4 Cell / 14.8VDischarge:65C Constant / 130C BurstWeight:527g (including wire, plug & case)Dimensions:153 x 49 x 33mmBalance Plug:JST-XHDischarge Plug:XT-90Advantages over traditional Lipoly batteries;• Power density reaches 7.5 kw/kg.• Less Voltage sag during high rate discharge, giving more power under load.• Internal impedance can reach as low as 1.2mO compared to that of 3mO of a standard Lipoly.• Greater thermal control, pack usually doesn’t exceed 60degC• Swelling during heavy load doesn’t exceed 5%, compared to 15% of a normal Lipoly.• Higher capacity during heavy discharge. More than 90% at 100% C rate.• Fast charge capable, up to 15C on some batteries.• Longer Cycle Life, almost double that of standard lipoly technology.The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

Title: RADIOMASTER (Charcoal) Pocket CC2500 FCC 2.4GHz Compact 16ch Transmitter w/Open-Source Edge TX Firmware
Description: The RADIOMASTER Pocket is a small, lightweight radio that packs a big punch and is full of features. It is available in two versions, ExpressLRS and CC2500 (see "Specs" for details), and both versions come with the cutting-edge EdgeTX firmware preinstalled. Also, both versions are available in either an FCC version or a European LBT version, once again, please check the "Specs" below for the supported protocol. For easy transport and storage, the lightweight Pocket transmitter is equipped with removable stick ends and a foldable antenna. It is also compatible with the popular 18650 batteries, these provide a long battery life for hours and hours of fun.Other features include high-quality Hall effect gimbals for smooth centering and precise response, trim buttons for easy trimming, built-in LED lights that help visualize your switch inputs, a backlit LCD Screen offering a perfect balance of size and functionality, and an external module bay compatible with RADIOMASTER Nano-size and TBS Nano Crossfire/Nano Tracer modules.The Edge TX open-source firmware is highly customizable, allowing users to configure their transmitters through the supplied USB-C data port to adjust the settings for their preferences and specific needs. EdgeTX supports a wide range of RC protocols and is a versatile and powerful tool, making it extremely popular with the RC community. RADIOMASTER works closely with the EdgeTX team to develop and optimize the user experience and will continue to ensure that the concept and standards are carried forward into the future.The Pocket is a small, versatile 16ch (receiver-dependent) transmitter that is a great choice for pilots looking for a radio with all the powerful features you have come to expect from RADIOMASTER.

Title: RADIOMASTER (Charcoal) Pocket CC2500 FCC 2.4GHz Compact 16ch Transmitter w/Open-Source Edge TX Firmware
Description: The RADIOMASTER Pocket is a small, lightweight radio that packs a big punch and is full of features. It is available in two versions, ExpressLRS and CC2500 (see "Specs" for details), and both versions come with the cutting-edge EdgeTX firmware preinstalled. Also, both versions are available in either an FCC version or a European LBT version, once again, please check the "Specs" below for the supported protocol. For easy transport and storage, the lightweight Pocket transmitter is equipped with removable stick ends and a foldable antenna. It is also compatible with the popular 18650 batteries, these provide a long battery life for hours and hours of fun.Other features include high-quality Hall effect gimbals for smooth centering and precise response, trim buttons for easy trimming, built-in LED lights that help visualize your switch inputs, a backlit LCD Screen offering a perfect balance of size and functionality, and an external module bay compatible with RADIOMASTER Nano-size and TBS Nano Crossfire/Nano Tracer modules.The Edge TX open-source firmware is highly customizable, allowing users to configure their transmitters through the supplied USB-C data port to adjust the settings for their preferences and specific needs. EdgeTX supports a wide range of RC protocols and is a versatile and powerful tool, making it extremely popular with the RC community. RADIOMASTER works closely with the EdgeTX team to develop and optimize the user experience and will continue to ensure that the concept and standards are carried forward into the future.The Pocket is a small, versatile 16ch (receiver-dependent) transmitter that is a great choice for pilots looking for a radio with all the powerful features you have come to expect from RADIOMASTER.

Title: RADIOMASTER MT12 4-in-1 FCC Surface Transmitter w/R85C Receiver
Description: The RADIOMASTER MT12 is a pioneering open-source surface radio, and the first surface radio officially supported by the EdgeTX and ExpressLRS multi-module project. The MT12 is available as either an ELRS or 4-in-1 multi-module version (see specs) and boasts 10 physical inputs, and the capability to handle either 16 or 32 channels (4-in-1 version only). The 4-in-1 system offers one transmitter for all of your cars, boats, or anything else that operates on the surface. The internal RF system has protocols, for many popular brands of cars and receivers (see below for the web address to the supported protocols). Each version is also available in either an FCC version or a European LBT version, please check the specifications below for the supported protocol.The EdgeTX system is preinstalled and the MT12 has cutting-edge software fit for its class-leading hardware. RADIOMASTER works closely with the EdgeTX team to develop new features and optimize the user experience for surface models. RADIOMASTER will also continue to contribute and support projects like EdgeTX, ensuring the concepts of open standards are carried forward, for more information, please visit https://edgetx.org/Just a few of the features of the MT12 include a standardized button layout and CNC menu wheel, adjustable throttle trigger to suit your driving style, adjustable wheel tension, Hall sensors for accurate inputs and precise centering, 5 trim buttons, and an external NANO module. Included with the transmitter is the R85C receiver, which is compatible with FrSky D8/D16 and Futaba SFHSS RADIOMASTER protocols, it also offers a receiving range that is suitable for most RC modeler's needs. It has a built-in TCXO (temperature compensated Xtal Oscillator), which ensures high stability and accuracy in frequency control whilst compensating for temperature variations.The MT12 is primed for a wide array of surface models, from cars and trucks to boats and much more. Featuring extensive customizability and a versatile operating system, the MT12 stands out as a highly configurable surface radio, prepared to excel in virtually any scenario.

This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion.Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.Advantages over traditional Lipo batteries:-Power density reaches 7.5 kw/kg.-Less Voltage sag during high rate discharge, giving more power under load.-Internal impedance can reach as low as 1.2mΩ compared to that of 3mΩ of a standardLipoly.-Greater thermal control, pack usually doesnt exceed 60degC-Thickness swelling during heavy load doesnt exceed 5%, compared to 15% of a normalLipolyduring heavy load.-Higher capacity during heavy discharge. More than 90% at 100% C rate.-Fast charge capable, up to 15C on some batteries.-Longer Cycle Life, almost double that of standard lipoly technology

Title: Turnigy Graphene Professional 3000mAh 3S 15C LiPo Pack w/XT60
Description: TURNIGY, the name synonymous with performance, reliability and innovation is excited to release a powerful new battery chemistry in the Turnigy Graphene!The Graphene Professional series is designed for professional UAV/RPA operators (unmanned Aerial Vehicle/Remotely Piloted Aircraft) and those that demand nothing less than the best.Graphene batteries are unlike anything you have seen or used before.Turnigy Graphene packs utilize carbon in the battery structure to form a single layer of graphene just 0.335nm thick, making that type of battery substrate the thinnest known to mankind. The graphene particles form a highly dense compound allowing electrons to flow with less resistance compared to traditional Lipoly battery technologies.The result is a battery capable of maintaining greater power output whilst remaining much cooler under load. Since heat and resistance are the natural enemy of batteries, Graphene chemistry has significantly reduced these problems and the result is an incredible boost in cycle life and performance.We have a full range of Graphene Professional battery packs and will be adding new sizes/configurations as they become available. Turnigy Graphene batteries are the new standard for serious professionals who require POWER ON DEMAND.

Title: RADIOMASTER TX16S MKII 4-in-1 Multi-protocol 16ch FCC 2.4GHz RC Transmitter w/AG01 Gimbals
Description: The best just got better, the RADIOMASTER TX16S MKII is the ultimate open-source radio. It is still a high-end, low-cost, OpenTx radio that has many great features, and this version includes the powerful long-range ELRS protocol. With the MKII you get many new features, these include, improved internal circuitry, AG01 quad-bearing Hall sensor gimbals for a smooth precise feel (this version only), improved ergonomics, redesigned battery cover, and improved knobs and sliders that are smoother with better center ident.The TX16S MKII transmitter supports EdgeTX and OpenTX open source firmware which is fully supported by the OpenTX development team. RADIOMASTER works closely with the EdgeTX team to develop and optimize the user experience and will continue to ensure that the concept and standards are carried forward into the future. The TX16S MKII is available in either an FCC version or a European LBT version, please check the specifications below for the supported protocol.There is a module slot in the back of the transmitter which will accept the popular JR/FrSky/TBS Crossfire type of module which means you can be up and running almost instantly with your favorite protocols. There is no need to remove the external module if you have one plugged in as the TX16S can be switched easily between the internal RF and the external RF. The transmitter is also Mode selectable so it can be either Mode 1 or Mode 2, this does, however, require the back being removed to move some mechanical components from one stick unit to the other.The supplied battery tray will accept either 2 x 3.7V 18650 Lithium-Ion batteries or 2 x 3.7V LiPo batteries. The large battery compartment (97x52x25mm) also has room for a 2S LiPo pack of your choice. A nice feature of this radio is that the batteries can stay in the compartment and be charged via the USB-C charging port. Another improvement of the MKII is that it now allows for charge rates of up to 2.2A. Other ports include a new 3.5mm audio jack, 3.5mm TRS trainer socket, a USB data port, SD card slot, and 2 UART ports to expand the capabilities of the radio.Overall this improved MKII version is an easy-to-use, multi-protocol transmitter that removes the need for you to have lots of different types of transmitters at your disposal. This one unit will operate just about all the different protocols on the market today.

Title: Turnigy Plush-32 60A (2~6S) Brushless Speed Controller w/BEC (Rev1.1.0)
Description: The Turnigy Plush-32 brushless ESC comes with a 32-bit ARM controller which offers higher resolution, makes it quicker, smoother, and more responsive to your throttle inputs. As you would expect, all the Turnigy Plush-32 are manufactured to the same high-quality standards that you have come to expect with all the Turnigy Plush ESCs.Now with the updated Rev1.1.0 firmware, these speed controllers offer a few more programming options over previous models. These include motor type, spool-up acceleration, PWM frequency, beacon delay, and an adjustable BEC (this is only available on the 150A). Most of these revisions are self-explanatory but the "Beacon Delay" does require an explanation. The "Beacon Delay" is quite a unique function that will cause the ESC to start "beeping" after a predetermined delay of not using the throttle stick, this can be set via the program card. The loud beeping noise is perfect for finding your model if it gets lost in high grass, standing crops, or in the bush, etc. Please note that you can use your existing Plush 32 programming card but you will not be able to access the revised functions unless you purchase the new Rev1.1.0 programming card.Programming your Plush 32 ESC is made very simple if you use the Plush 32 programming card. No more listening to the beeps, and guessing when to move your throttle, the programming card changes settings with the press of a button. Easy-to-read LEDs let you know exactly how your ESC is being programmed and set. So don’t forget to include a programming card when purchasing your ESC, see related products.

Title: RADIOMASTER MT12 4-in-1 FCC Surface Transmitter w/R85C Receiver
Description: The RADIOMASTER MT12 is a pioneering open-source surface radio, and the first surface radio officially supported by the EdgeTX and ExpressLRS multi-module project. The MT12 is available as either an ELRS or 4-in-1 multi-module version (see specs) and boasts 10 physical inputs, and the capability to handle either 16 or 32 channels (4-in-1 version only). The 4-in-1 system offers one transmitter for all of your cars, boats, or anything else that operates on the surface. The internal RF system has protocols, for many popular brands of cars and receivers (see below for the web address to the supported protocols). Each version is also available in either an FCC version or a European LBT version, please check the specifications below for the supported protocol.The EdgeTX system is preinstalled and the MT12 has cutting-edge software fit for its class-leading hardware. RADIOMASTER works closely with the EdgeTX team to develop new features and optimize the user experience for surface models. RADIOMASTER will also continue to contribute and support projects like EdgeTX, ensuring the concepts of open standards are carried forward, for more information, please visit https://edgetx.org/Just a few of the features of the MT12 include a standardized button layout and CNC menu wheel, adjustable throttle trigger to suit your driving style, adjustable wheel tension, Hall sensors for accurate inputs and precise centering, 5 trim buttons, and an external NANO module. Included with the transmitter is the R85C receiver, which is compatible with FrSky D8/D16 and Futaba SFHSS RADIOMASTER protocols, it also offers a receiving range that is suitable for most RC modeler's needs. It has a built-in TCXO (temperature compensated Xtal Oscillator), which ensures high stability and accuracy in frequency control whilst compensating for temperature variations.The MT12 is primed for a wide array of surface models, from cars and trucks to boats and much more. Featuring extensive customizability and a versatile operating system, the MT12 stands out as a highly configurable surface radio, prepared to excel in virtually any scenario.

Title: XK (RTF) K100 6ch CP Micro 3D Helicopter w/Switchable 3/6-Axis Gyro & Hover Mode
Description: The XK K100 6ch CP palm-size helicopter with collective pitch is the perfect choice for those pilots who want to progress on their journey of learning to fly RC helicopters. The K100 CP is very capable of performing advanced aerobatics and 3D flight, but it is also equally at home flying as a stable intermediate training platform. Using a state-of-the-art switchable gyro stabilization system, it has the ability to be switched from 6-axis for super stable flight, to 3-axis for aerobatics and wild 3D flight. Also, when you select the 6-axis gyro system, you can select "Hover Mode", at the flick of a switch on the transmitter the K100 will sit in a stable hover without any inputs from you on the control sticks.Included in the box is everything you need to get flying, a 2.4Ghz 6ch transmitter with a large LCD screen for programming different settings, a 3.7V 300mAh 25C LiPo battery, and a USB charging system that is capable of charging 2 batteries simultaneously. The transmitter has the ability to be easily switched to operate as either Mode 1 or Mode 2, these modes give you the choice of which control functions are on which control sticks. Also included are some tools, spare parts, and an informative instruction manual.Another quite unique feature for a small ready-to-fly helicopter is that it can be flown if you wish using a Futaba S-FHSS radio system. This will appeal to experienced pilots who would like to use their own Futaba computer radio to fly the XK K100. A powerful 8520 coreless motor supplies power to the main rotors, and this coupled with the K100 being manufactured to the highest of standards using high-quality components, makes this a must-have heli for the intermediate to experienced RC pilot.

Title: GOOSKY (BNF) Legend S2 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter S-FHSS/DSMX (Blue/Green)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S2 is a game-changing, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique one-piece concave CNC bracket for the swashplate actuator system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for low-time and experienced pilots alike.This BNF (Bind-N-Fly) version of the Legend S2 is supplied not only with the servos and flight controller but a built-in S-FHSS protocol, S-BUS/PPM receiver as well. This receiver is compatible with Futaba out of the box, but it can also be used with DSMX systems, this will require a DSMX-compatible satellite receiver (not supplied). The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precision control with two flight modes. Out of the box, the 2 factory set defaults allow for either a sedate, quiet flying machine on the fully stabilized setting, or change into the advanced setting to unleash a wild and exciting 3D aerobatic machine. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler.Other features include a quick-release tail rotor blade system, CNC machined metal parts for reinforcement of the frame, fixed length pushrods for accurate set-up, tough one-piece landing gear, high-strength alloy tail boom, and a unique tail boom holder design to help minimize damage in a crash.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to bind to your own transmitter and is quick and simple to set up via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S2 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning, tough, and well-engineered helicopter.

Title: Turnigy nano-tech 4000mAh 4S 45~90C Lipo Pack w/XT-90
Description: Suited to the following models:Hirobo Lepton EX, HIROBO SDX-EP(4S x 2)More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. Utilizing an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and a higher discharge rates than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) batteries.For those that love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves and excellent performance. For pilots it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance.Lithium Polymer batteries are used in many RC hobby industries. Over the last few years, Lipo batteries have become the most popular battery choice for anyone looking for a longer run time and higher power.Lipo batteries weigh less and can be made into almost any size or shape. Lipo batteries have higher capacities, hold more power and have a higher discharge rate, meaning they pack more punch. For safe use and storage of Lipo batteries, you need to follow the rules and treat the batteries with the respect they deserve.The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

Title: RADIOMASTER RP3 V2 FCC ExpressLRS 2.4GHz Nano Receiver
Description: The RadioMaster RP V2 series of receivers now have a built-in TCXO (Temperature-Compensated Xtal Oscillator). The TCXO ensures high stability and accuracy in frequency control and compensates for temperature variations. This results in consistent and reliable signal reception, even in extreme temperature conditions. It also reduces frequency drift over time, providing long-term frequency stability and preventing signal degradation. This provides a superior performance in demanding environments and enhances the flight experiences.The RP3 2.4GHz ELRS Nano receivers use the high-performance, revolutionary ExpressLRS open-source system. The ExpressLRS development team designed the Nano receivers, which feature the ESP8285 MCU and SX1280 RF chips. This offers Lora and FLRC 2.4GHz RF links for incredible range and low latency. WiFi is built-in to easily upgrade the firmware and configure the receiver using your PC or mobile phone.The receiver features a Skyworks SE2431L providing an LNA for improved receiver performance, a PA providing up to 100mW of telemetry performance, and antenna switching for antenna diversity. The RP3 Nano receiver is available in either an FCC or a European LBT version, please check the specifications below for the supported protocol.

Title: Aerostar 130A HV RVS G2 32bit (6~14S) Opto Electronic Speed Controller w/Reverse Function
Description: The Aerostar RVS G2 next-generation range of HV Opto brushless speed controllers moves these amazing ESCs up a notch from the ground-breaking original Aerostar RVS HV ESCs. New generation MOSFETs with the aid of the highly efficient cooling fan and finned, aluminum heatsink, ensure that the ESC stays within operating temperatures at all times, and can also safely handle the peak current draw specified. They process much faster due to the high-performance 32bit M4 microprocessor running at 170MHz, and have improved functionality and programmable features. Our RVS (reverse function system) is now instantaneous, with no need for the motor to stop turning, this makes it perfect for EDF braking (reverse thrust), and waterplanes for taxiing, etc. If you don't require the reverse function, simply do not connect the second lead to your receiver, it will then operate as a standard ESC.The Aerostar RVS G2 HV brushless speed controllers have been designed for a range of fixed-wing applications including as mentioned above, EDF braking/reverse thrust, floatplane/flying boat operations, and with the soft-start function, geared motors using large standard or folding propellers. Another feature of the G2 range of ESC is the addition of HEF (Higher-Efficiency Function) technology. The HEF circuitry allows for better heat dissipation, and lower energy loss when used with certain applications, this function when selected is very similar to "Active Freewheeling". When set to "Off" (the factory default) it's perfect for low to medium KV outrunner motors, when set to "On", it's perfect for high KV outrunners, and inrunners such as those used in EDFs or direct drive racing models.Features that have been retained from the original version are the super smooth start-up, linear throttle response, and multiple protection features. These protections include start-up (prevents motor accidentally starting when powering up), low-voltage cut-off, phase loss, and signal loss, to fully protect the components of your ESC. Programming the many functions of the Aerostar RVS G2 HV ESC is very simple using either your transmitter, the optional LCD programming card, or exclusive to the HV series the Aerostar App in conjunction with the optional Bluetooth module.Being an "Opto" ESC it does not include a BEC/SBEC system, it will require a separate power source to power your servos and receiver, etc. This high-quality opto-coupling system uses light signals to transfer the electronic data that is provided by the receiver to the power circuit that drives the motor. This opto-isolation enhances safety by preventing electrical interference between the motor and the sensitive electronic control components.

Title: Turnigy Nano-Tech 3300mAh 6S 45C Lipo Pack w/XT90
Description: More than just a fancy name the TURNIGY Nano-Tech lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. Utilising an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and a higher discharge rate than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) battery.For those that love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves and excellent performance. For pilots it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance, this is excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged but be rest assured, TURNIGY Nano-Techs are the real deal, they deliver unparalleled performance time and time again!The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

GOOSKY (RTF) Mode 1 Legend S2 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter (Yellow)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S2 is a game-changing, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique one-piece concave CNC bracket for the swashplate actuator system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for low-time and experienced pilots alike.This RTF (Ready-to-Fly) version of the Legend S2 is not only supplied with metal-geared servos, flight controller, and battery but a dedicated, simple-to-use GOOSKY T8 transmitter as well. This transmitter is squarely aimed at the novice pilot, with no complicated computer programming, basically just switch it on and fly, but it is also perfect for the more experienced pilot who just wants to get flying quickly and easily. Out of the box, the 2 factory set defaults allow for either a sedate, quiet flying machine on the fully stabilized setting, or flick the Tx flight mode switch into the advanced setting to unleash a wild and exciting 3D aerobatic machine. The transmitter is Mode 1, meaning that the throttle and left/right cyclic are on the right stick, and fore/aft cyclic and tail rotor are on the left stick. The T8 also includes its own 3.7V 18650 2800mAh battery which is easily charged via the Type-C USB port in the side of the transmitter.The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precise control of the two flight modes as mentioned above. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler. The T8 transmitter uses the popular S-FHSS protocol which the GTS system is set up for, however, it can also be matched to a DSMX system if you wish by adding a DSMX-compatible satellite receiver.Other features include a quick-release tail rotor blade system, CNC machined metal parts for reinforcement of the frame, fixed length pushrods for accurate set-up, tough one-piece landing gear, high-strength alloy tail boom, and a unique tail boom holder design to help minimize damage in a crash.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to fly, you just need to charge the battery and away you go. If you need to change the default settings, then this is quick and simple via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S2 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning, tough, and well-engineered helicopter.

Title: RADIOMASTER RP3 V2 FCC ExpressLRS 2.4GHz Nano Receiver
Description: The RadioMaster RP V2 series of receivers now have a built-in TCXO (Temperature-Compensated Xtal Oscillator). The TCXO ensures high stability and accuracy in frequency control and compensates for temperature variations. This results in consistent and reliable signal reception, even in extreme temperature conditions. It also reduces frequency drift over time, providing long-term frequency stability and preventing signal degradation. This provides a superior performance in demanding environments and enhances the flight experiences.The RP3 2.4GHz ELRS Nano receivers use the high-performance, revolutionary ExpressLRS open-source system. The ExpressLRS development team designed the Nano receivers, which feature the ESP8285 MCU and SX1280 RF chips. This offers Lora and FLRC 2.4GHz RF links for incredible range and low latency. WiFi is built-in to easily upgrade the firmware and configure the receiver using your PC or mobile phone.The receiver features a Skyworks SE2431L providing an LNA for improved receiver performance, a PA providing up to 100mW of telemetry performance, and antenna switching for antenna diversity. The RP3 Nano receiver is available in either an FCC or a European LBT version, please check the specifications below for the supported protocol.

Title: GOOSKY (RTF) Mode 1 Legend S2 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter (Yellow)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S2 is a game-changing, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique one-piece concave CNC bracket for the swashplate actuator system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for low-time and experienced pilots alike.This RTF (Ready-to-Fly) version of the Legend S2 is not only supplied with metal-geared servos, flight controller, and battery but a dedicated, simple-to-use GOOSKY T8 transmitter as well. This transmitter is squarely aimed at the novice pilot, with no complicated computer programming, basically just switch it on and fly, but it is also perfect for the more experienced pilot who just wants to get flying quickly and easily. Out of the box, the 2 factory set defaults allow for either a sedate, quiet flying machine on the fully stabilized setting, or flick the Tx flight mode switch into the advanced setting to unleash a wild and exciting 3D aerobatic machine. The transmitter is Mode 1, meaning that the throttle and left/right cyclic are on the right stick, and fore/aft cyclic and tail rotor are on the left stick. The T8 also includes its own 3.7V 18650 2800mAh battery which is easily charged via the Type-C USB port in the side of the transmitter.The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precise control of the two flight modes as mentioned above. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler. The T8 transmitter uses the popular S-FHSS protocol which the GTS system is set up for, however, it can also be matched to a DSMX system if you wish by adding a DSMX-compatible satellite receiver.Other features include a quick-release tail rotor blade system, CNC machined metal parts for reinforcement of the frame, fixed length pushrods for accurate set-up, tough one-piece landing gear, high-strength alloy tail boom, and a unique tail boom holder design to help minimize damage in a crash.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to fly, you just need to charge the battery and away you go. If you need to change the default settings, then this is quick and simple via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S2 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning, tough, and well-engineered helicopter.

Title: FLYSKY FRM302 2.4GHz AFHDS 3 Long Range Transmitter Module PL18/NV14 Compatible w/PPM/UART Modes
Description: The FTM302 adopts FLYSKY's third-generation automatic frequency hopping digital system, AFHDS 3. It uses a single antenna, a bidirectional transmission system in a compact design with support for multiple signal inputs. Supports external power and is compatible with standard JR-type module bays.The FTM302 offers a long range of up to 3.5km + on the EU default setting of 20dBm (changeable through the management system), low latency, less than 10ms, and allows for online updates and managing the module via the FLYSKY Remote Control Assistant. Power to the module can either be internal or an external power source of 5~28V via the built-in XT30 connector. The module also has a built-in fan which automatically turns on if the temperature reaches 45°C to ensure the system remains safe, this can happen when the module is being used with higher voltages.High-gain RF components, coupled with the 2.4GHz AFHDS 3 protocol, enable the module to cut through interference easily while maintaining high transmission rates, especially when compared to 900MHz counterparts. The FRM302 uses FLYSKY's latest generation of intelligent wireless protocol (AFHDS 3) to achieve higher sensitivity and higher gain. It achieves high-speed data transmission and low latency of 10ms in UART mode. This gives a precise response in weak signal conditions and active evasion of co-channel interference, especially when being used at extreme ranges and areas with multiple obstacles.The FRM302 supports PPM and UART serial communication modes with failsafe, settings can be changed at the touch of a button, and the antenna can be replaced for customized applications. The FRM302 module is compatible with FTr16, FTr10, and all other AFHDS 3 receivers. So with regular online updates via the RC assistant, a wide range of the latest technology features, and FLYSKY's attention to quality and detail, this is a must for all FPV/UAV and drone pilots.

Title: FLYSKY FRM302 2.4GHz AFHDS 3 Long Range Transmitter Module PL18/NV14 Compatible w/PPM/UART Modes
Description: The FTM302 adopts FLYSKY's third-generation automatic frequency hopping digital system, AFHDS 3. It uses a single antenna, a bidirectional transmission system in a compact design with support for multiple signal inputs. Supports external power and is compatible with standard JR-type module bays.The FTM302 offers a long range of up to 3.5km + on the EU default setting of 20dBm (changeable through the management system), low latency, less than 10ms, and allows for online updates and managing the module via the FLYSKY Remote Control Assistant. Power to the module can either be internal or an external power source of 5~28V via the built-in XT30 connector. The module also has a built-in fan which automatically turns on if the temperature reaches 45°C to ensure the system remains safe, this can happen when the module is being used with higher voltages.High-gain RF components, coupled with the 2.4GHz AFHDS 3 protocol, enable the module to cut through interference easily while maintaining high transmission rates, especially when compared to 900MHz counterparts. The FRM302 uses FLYSKY's latest generation of intelligent wireless protocol (AFHDS 3) to achieve higher sensitivity and higher gain. It achieves high-speed data transmission and low latency of 10ms in UART mode. This gives a precise response in weak signal conditions and active evasion of co-channel interference, especially when being used at extreme ranges and areas with multiple obstacles.The FRM302 supports PPM and UART serial communication modes with failsafe, settings can be changed at the touch of a button, and the antenna can be replaced for customized applications. The FRM302 module is compatible with FTr16, FTr10, and all other AFHDS 3 receivers. So with regular online updates via the RC assistant, a wide range of the latest technology features, and FLYSKY's attention to quality and detail, this is a must for all FPV/UAV and drone pilots.

Title: Dancing Wings Hobby (Kit) Aion 2500mm Laser Cut Balsa EP Sport Glider w/Motor, ESC, Servos, Prop & Film Pack
Description: The Dancing Wings Hobby Aion laser cut balsa kit is an easy-build electric sports glider that includes ailerons and flaps. The Aion is aimed at the modeler who wants to experience real model-making but wants something that is reasonably straightforward to build. This is achieved with the use of accurate laser-cut parts and the simple box-type fuselage which produce a strong, accurate, lightweight structure. The Aion is relatively easy to build, however, we do recommend that some experience in building a wood model airplane has been gained previously. Most of the components are constructed over the detailed, high-quality printed 1:1 building plan.The Aion is a large wingspan (2.5M) electric sport glider that is quite happy to fly around under power doing gentle aerobatics, and it is equally at home with the power off soaring away in thermals on a nice sunny day. It has ailerons, elevator, and rudder control, plus it has flaps, these are great for soaring, or used as crow-braking to reduce the float for nice short spot landings.This outstanding kit is supplied with a powerful 2216-920KV brushless motor, a 30A brushless ESC, an 11" folding prop with a metal spinner, 6 x 9g servos, and an iron-on covering film pack. Once the airframe is built, we recommend that you cover the model in the lightweight, iron-on covering supplied as shown in the pictures. The solid white on the fuselage, and the transparent colors on the open structures. This shows off the beautiful structure of the wings and tail components and looks great when flying with the sun shining through.So either take a trip down memory lane and get away from all the foamies or ARTFs, or experience building your first model from a kit. The kit itself includes laser-cut parts, ample strip wood, carbon dihedral braces, a decal sheet, and a complete hardware pack.

Title: GOOSKY (RTF) Mode 1 Legend S2 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter (Red/Yellow)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S2 is a game-changing, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique one-piece concave CNC bracket for the swashplate actuator system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for low-time and experienced pilots alike.This RTF (Ready-to-Fly) version of the Legend S2 is not only supplied with metal-geared servos, flight controller, and battery but a dedicated, simple-to-use GOOSKY T8 transmitter as well. This transmitter is squarely aimed at the novice pilot, with no complicated computer programming, basically just switch it on and fly, but it is also perfect for the more experienced pilot who just wants to get flying quickly and easily. Out of the box, the 2 factory set defaults allow for either a sedate, quiet flying machine on the fully stabilized setting, or flick the Tx flight mode switch into the advanced setting to unleash a wild and exciting 3D aerobatic machine. The transmitter is Mode 1, meaning that the throttle and left/right cyclic are on the right stick, and fore/aft cyclic and tail rotor are on the left stick. The T8 also includes its own 3.7V 18650 2800mAh battery which is easily charged via the Type-C USB port in the side of the transmitter.The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precise control of the two flight modes as mentioned above. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler. The T8 transmitter uses the popular S-FHSS protocol which the GTS system is set up for, however, it can also be matched to a DSMX system if you wish by adding a DSMX-compatible satellite receiver.Other features include a quick-release tail rotor blade system, CNC machined metal parts for reinforcement of the frame, fixed length pushrods for accurate set-up, tough one-piece landing gear, high-strength alloy tail boom, and a unique tail boom holder design to help minimize damage in a crash.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to fly, you just need to charge the battery and away you go. If you need to change the default settings, then this is quick and simple via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S2 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning, tough, and well-engineered helicopter.

Description: More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. Utilizing an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and higher discharge rates than similar density lithium polymer (non-nano-tech) batteries.For those that love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves, and excellent performance. For pilots, it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings, and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!The nano-core technology in lithium-ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high-rate discharge decreases greatly.

Description: Based on the amazing GOOSKY Legend RS4, the RS4 Venom Edition boasts major updates in features and design. Title: GOOSKY (BNF) Legend S1 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter S-FHSS/DSMX (Green)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S1 is a small, game-changing, high-performance, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique "cage body" metal geared servo system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the designers in producing a tough, easy-to-fly, maintenance-free, high-performance helicopter suitable for entry-level and experienced pilots alike.This BNF (Bind-N-Fly) version of the Legend S1 is supplied not only with the servos and flight controller but a built-in S-FHSS protocol, and S-BUS/PPM receiver as well. This receiver is compatible with Futaba out of the box, but it can also be used with DSMX systems, this will require a DSMX-compatible satellite receiver (not supplied). The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precision control with two flight modes. Mode 1 is self-stabilization that offers amazing stability for the beginner, and Mode 2 allows for high-performance aerobatics and full 3D flight. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler.This incredible little helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to bind to your own transmitter, is quick and simple to set up via the GOOSKY APP, and most importantly, it is exciting, and great fun to fly.

Turnigy TGY-i6S Mode 2 Digital Proportional Radio Control System (Black)
Description: As the old saying goes, the best just got better. This is definitely the case with the Turnigy TGY-i6S as it builds on the already great Turnigy-i6. The TGY-i6S still uses the solid and reliable 2.4GHz Automatic Frequency Hopping Digital System (AFHDS) spread spectrum technology. It is also a superb budget radio for both new and experienced pilots and is designed with multi-rotor / drone flying in mind. It can also be used for planes/gliders.The Turnigy TGY-i6S is a 6-channel (PWM) or a 10-channel (PPM)  2.4GHz AFHDS Digital Proportional RC system. It comes complete with two receivers, the dependable TGY-iA6B 6 channel receiver and the new TGY-iA6C receiver for PPM or SBUS.The new look design comes with some exciting new features. This radio incorporates a monochrome backlit LCD touchscreen making it easy to program and make changes in sunlight or at night. There are two internal dual omnidirectional high gain antennas (for more reliability) built inside the frame so they can’t be damaged in transit. To help control your aircraft there are lots of programmable switches, buttons, and scroll wheels. Making them great for setting up flight modes and the scroll wheels could be used for controlling camera gimbals.The ergonomically designed case makes for easy use of all controls. All switches and scroll wheels are within easy reach and the adjustable length sticks can be set for comfortable use.  There is a loop for attaching a neck strap and a phone/monitor holder mounting point. There is even a mini USB port for easy connection to your PC for updates or for connecting (via USB) to your favorite simulator programs.Each transmitter and receiver has its own unique ID. Once the transmitter and receiver have been paired, they will only communicate with each other, preventing other systems from accidentally connecting to or interfering with the system's operation. Each transmitter hops between 16 channels in order to reduce interference from other transmitters.The TGY-i6S comes in either Mode 1 and Mode 2 and is available in black or white for each mode.With all the features the TGY-i6S offers, it is one of the best radios available, dollar for dollar.

Title: PLA Premium Clear 1kg 1.75mm HobbyKing
Description: Print incredible structures and 3D projects with HobbyKing's own range of PLA filament. If you're new to using PLA, you'll find it easier to print thanks to having a lower melting point.One of the most important features is that PLA is non-toxic with an extremely high printing resolution. . PLA has a low shrinkage rate and is very rigid with minimal flex. While PLA is considered stronger than ABS it is more susceptible to cracking when subjected to flexing, therefore you will need to consider if the filament is right for the mechanical needs of the print project.A great material for 3D printing, PLA can be printed without the use of a heat bead and can stick to glass or a PCB plate using a binder such as hairspray or white glue.  These simple binding agents will help achieve a curl free print.3D printing is a fun and exciting hobby with a wide range of uses from prototyping parts to making toys for the kids. Picking the right filament for your application is very important. HobbyKing filaments have a stable melting point, good round shape and most importantly a 0.05mm uniform diameter tolerance for a consistent flow rate.

Title: Hobbywing XRotor Multi-Rotor ESC Opto 15A
Description: The Hobbywing XRotor 15A speed controller has been designed specifically for multi-rotor applications. It comes with a 32bit MCU which increases responce times. Besides regular throttle signals with a refresh rate below 500Hz, the XRotor 15A ESC also supports OneShot mode throttle signals. Title: Turnigy Plush-32 150A (2~6S) Brushless Speed Controller w/BEC (Rev1.1.0)
Description: The Turnigy Plush-32 brushless ESC comes with a 32-bit ARM controller which offers higher resolution, makes it quicker, smoother, and more responsive to your throttle inputs. As you would expect, all the Turnigy Plush-32 are manufactured to the same high-quality standards that you have come to expect with all the Turnigy Plush ESCs.Now with the updated Rev1.1.0 firmware, these speed controllers offer a few more programming options over previous models. These include motor type, spool-up acceleration, PWM frequency, beacon delay, and an adjustable BEC (this is only available on the 150A). Most of these revisions are self-explanatory but the "Beacon Delay" does require an explanation. The "Beacon Delay" is quite a unique function that will cause the ESC to start "beeping" after a predetermined delay of not using the throttle stick, this can be set via the program card. The loud beeping noise is perfect for finding your model if it gets lost in high grass, standing crops, or in the bush, etc. Please note that you can use your existing Plush 32 programming card but you will not be able to access the revised functions unless you purchase the new Rev1.1.0 programming card.Programming your Plush 32 ESC is made very simple if you use the Plush 32 programming card. No more listening to the beeps, and guessing when to move your throttle, the programming card changes settings with the press of a button. Easy-to-read LEDs let you know exactly how your ESC is being programmed and set. So don’t forget to include a programming card when purchasing your ESC, see related products.

Description: The top of the range, 16 Channel X8R receiver from FrSky with 8 normal PWM outputs and no less than 16 channels on the dedicated S.BUS output.The X8R is a surprisingly compact package compared to many 8 channel receivers and has all of the amazing functionality associated with FrSky products. The Smart Port supports the new hub-less sensors in addition to the older hub analog sensors.The X8R supports 8 standard servo outputs, with a further 8 being available by using the S.Bus line with S.Bus supported servos or use a FrSky S.Bus Decoder, giving you a total of 16 channels. Alternatively, you can use two X8R receivers in combination and the channels will sync 1-8 on the first and 9-16 on the second. The second option will give a fantastic degree of redundancy, essential when flying large models and highly desirable in any event.The X8 protocol is backward compatible, so that in D8 mode it works with the DHT, DJT, DFT and DHT-U transmitter modules. This mode you facilitate a total of 8 channels and all of the Smart Port functions so that you can still use the full range of digital sensors.The PCB antenna has been recorded as providing up to a 20% gain in range over traditional and to save weight, these antennas do not have an external case.This is an outstanding receiver for all applications and is perfect for use with the FrSky Horus, X9D and X9E Taranis transmitters, with their built-in XJT Module or any of the D8 systems to take advantage of the new digital Smart Port sensors.The firmware of the X8R receiver can be upgraded by using the USB upgrade cables available separately (please see related items.)

Title: RC ERA (RTF) C129 V2 4ch Flybarless Micro 3D RC Helicopter w/Tx, 6-Axis Gyro & Barometric Altitude Hold
Description: This palm-sized RC Era C129 V2 takes all the latest in RC technology and packs it into a feature-filled, user-friendly, easy-to-fly micro helicopter. The flybarless system coupled with the 6-axis gyro stabilization unit gives it a stability not seen in many helicopters of this size before. The included 2.4GHz transmitter gives you full control of the helicopter, it allows you to climb or descend, fly backward and forwards, fly left and right, and rotate both ways around its axis. The new style V2 transmitter also includes a one-key 3D feature making for even more fun flying, and a 3-step flight mode button.One of the features that will help beginners immensely is an auto take-off and landing button, a single press of the one-key button will make the helicopter take off to an altitude of about 1.5 meters, press the same button again and it will safely land. Then there is the "Altitude Hold", which is controlled via a barometric sensor, the helicopter will hold any height you set and will stay there when the throttle stick is set at neutral. To move to a new altitude simply move the throttle stick up or down until you reach the altitude you want, return the stick to neutral and it will stay there until you move the throttle stick again.Being flybarless reduces the risk of damage to the helicopter in the event of a crash and also increases the flight time due to less drag. The included 300mAh 25C 1-cell modular battery is quick and easy to install and gives the C129 V2 an amazing duration of up to 15 minutes. This modular battery is charged using the supplied USB charger, which provides a fast and stable charge process. This V2 version has been upgraded with even more power, the robust 8520 coreless main motor gives it an abundance of power, and the nifty 0615 coreless tail motor is powerful and super reliable. The C129 V2 is manufactured using upgraded high-performance components and materials which further improve the strength and impact resistance, this is a small heli that is made to last.

Title: Turnigy Plush-32 150A (2~6S) Brushless Speed Controller w/BEC (Rev1.1.0)
Description: The Turnigy Plush-32 brushless ESC comes with a 32-bit ARM controller which offers higher resolution, makes it quicker, smoother, and more responsive to your throttle inputs. As you would expect, all the Turnigy Plush-32 are manufactured to the same high-quality standards that you have come to expect with all the Turnigy Plush ESCs.Now with the updated Rev1.1.0 firmware, these speed controllers offer a few more programming options over previous models. These include motor type, spool-up acceleration, PWM frequency, beacon delay, and an adjustable BEC (this is only available on the 150A). Most of these revisions are self-explanatory but the "Beacon Delay" does require an explanation. The "Beacon Delay" is quite a unique function that will cause the ESC to start "beeping" after a predetermined delay of not using the throttle stick, this can be set via the program card. The loud beeping noise is perfect for finding your model if it gets lost in high grass, standing crops, or in the bush, etc. Please note that you can use your existing Plush 32 programming card but you will not be able to access the revised functions unless you purchase the new Rev1.1.0 programming card.Programming your Plush 32 ESC is made very simple if you use the Plush 32 programming card. No more listening to the beeps, and guessing when to move your throttle, the programming card changes settings with the press of a button. Easy-to-read LEDs let you know exactly how your ESC is being programmed and set. So don’t forget to include a programming card when purchasing your ESC, see related products.

Title: XK A500 (RTF) QF F4U Corsair 3ch RC Cartoon Plane w/2.4GHz Tx & 6-Axis Gyro 350mm
Description: This fun little ready-to-fly cartoon version of an F4U Corsair WW2 fighter plane looks great and flies great. This is due to its built-in switchable 6-axis gyro flight stabilization system that makes it perfect for both beginners and experts who want a small model that is just that little bit different. It is tough too, it's constructed from durable, crash-resistant EPP foam which is light, extremely strong, and ready to take all the knocks and bangs associated with learning to fly.The 6-axis stabilization system is switchable via the transmitter from beginners mode which limits the amount of pitch and roll, plus it self-stabilizes, to 3D mode. This will allow the QF F4U to carry out a whole host of aerobatic maneuvers such as rolls and loops. The gyro stabilization system is controlled by a push button on top of the transmitter. If you have 3D mode selected and get into a muddle whilst flying, a simple press of the button will return the model to the fully stabilized mode and it will return to normal level flight. The supplied transmitter also has an aileron and elevator rates function, once again this is a simple push button that will increase, or decrease the amount of throw of the control surfaces. Also included is a fail-safe system which will prevent any flyaways if the signal is lost between the transmitter and receiver.The QF F4U Corsair takes minutes to assemble, simply connect the aileron servo lead and attach the wing, then clip in the main landing gear legs, and the tailwheel. The model takes off nicely from a smooth surface, or it can be hand-launched if you wish as it is quite happy flying without the wheels for a more realistic look in the air.If you wish to fly the QF F4U with your own transmitter then the included receiver/gyro board can operate with Futaba S-BUS receivers or any other receivers with S-BUS ports. It will also work with multi-protocol transmitters if the correct protocol is set, details in the user manual.The model is supplied with everything you need to fly out of the box (except Tx batteries) including a spare quick-release propeller with prop saver and spinner, a 3.7V 400mAh battery with USB charger, and a screwdriver set.

Description: More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipo batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. Utilizing an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and a higher discharge rate than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) batteries.For those that love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves and excellent performance. For pilots, it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!This particular battery has a 2-pin Molex connector. Please refer to the attached image as this Battery has the "B" plug polarity. Please make sure this battery suits your connection. The wrong polarity will damage your electronics.The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultrastrong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity. These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels.This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

Title: GOOSKY (COMBO VERSION) Legend RS4 Flybarless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter Kit (Pink)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend RS4 is a powerful 380-class, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, high-power direct-drive main motor, belt-driven tail rotor system, 2nd generation GTS flight controller with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, and a 70A intelligent speed controller with slow start. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for high-end 3D and aerobatic flying.The Legend RS4 is supplied as an unassembled kit that does require assembly, but being the combo version it is supplied with everything you need (apart from assembly tools) to get you flying apart from a transmitter, receiver, and a LiPo battery charger. The power system at the heart of the RS4 is a high-performance iron core, hand-wound brushless motor with high-speed bearings and NdFeB magnets. This motor coupled with the supplied 6S battery, and the 70A continuous intelligent speed controller, brings an infinite amount of power for even the most demanding of pilots.The GTS flight control system utilizes 2nd generation algorithmic technology for precision control of the flybarless head and tail rotor. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP using the supplied Bluetooth module, this makes setting up and fine-tuning a breeze. The ingenious design of the center structure with built-in bearing alignment brings strength and support to the cyclic control system, and the supplied metal-geared high-power servos provide a precise, fast, and accurate control response.Other features of the Legend RS4 include high-strength aluminum alloy main blade grips, high-precision tail rotor design with O-ring damping and a unique monorail-guided tail control system, an angled battery compartment for quick battery changes, strong thick-walled tail boom for stability in aggressive 3D flying, and a high strength, lightweight one-piece landing gear.This incredibly powerful 3D helicopter is a must-have for all experienced RC heli pilots, it will deliver thrilling flights, outstanding performance, and unforgettable aerial adventures.

Title: Turnigy Nano-Tech 1500mAh 3S 30C Lipo (E-flite Compatible EFLB15003S)
Description: This nano-tech battery pack offers 100mAh more capacity than the original Dynamite option battery and a much higher discharge rate. More punch, more power and longer drive times are only the beginning. When tested with the Dynamite DYN1477 the differences between the original battery and the nano-tech where remarkable! Out of the corner power was remarkable due to the extra capacity and C rate of this battery.The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels.This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

Title: H-King Bixler 2 EPO 1500mm (59") Glider ARF
Description: Looking for the perfect trainer? Or an in-expensive FPV platform? Maybe you are a club pilot looking for something you can just pull out of the car and fly on one of those lazy Sunday afternoons? The Hobbyking® ™ Bixler® ™ 2 ticks all of these boxes and more! The Bixler® ™ 2 has had some improvements to make it even better such as a bigger air inlet for better motor cooling.This version of the Bixler® ™ 2 comes as a "Kit" which means that you will need a motor, ESC, servos, 6CH 2.4GHz radio system, a 3S 2200mAh lipoly battery, and a battery charger. Just finish the assembly of the plane, set up your radio system and add your battery, power up the model, and fly. It's that easy!The Bixler® ™ 2 has all the right ingredients, starting with super tough EPO foam. The combination of size, low wing loading, and a sleek fuselage makes for an excellent model with capable yet forgiving flight characteristics. The plug-in wing makes the Bixler® ™ a practical model that is easy to transport to your favorite flying field and can be ready to fly in just minutes. Another practical feature of the Bixler® ™ 2 is its ability to accept a wide range of Lipoly sizes and/or FPV equipment courtesy of the enlarged canopy area. The Bixler® ™ 2 also comes with optional flaps which are pre-hinged (servos not included). The flaps are particularly ideal for FPV pilots carrying a heavier payload.The larger wing, flaps & much larger canopy area mean that the Bixler® ™ 2 is now so much more versatile in terms of FPV use and for new pilots and experienced pilots alike who are simply flying for fun, these new design features, combined with the larger, more efficient prop mean that the Bixler® ™ 2 offers longer flight times. However you decide to fly the Bixler® ™ 2, you can be assured that it is still just as easy and fun to fly as ever!

Title: Universal 2 Part Epoxy Repair Putty (30g)
Description: A must for every toolbox, this cold setting epoxy putty will repair just about anything. Uses include repairing metals, plastics, wood, glass, ceramics and masonry etc. It comes in with 2 sticks, one has the properties of epoxy resin and one has the properties of the hardner. To use you cut equal quantities off of each stick and knead them together, they have different colors, one being blue and the other yellow, when you have a green color they are mixed properly. The putty is now ready for use, it moulds like ordinary putty but when cured it sets like rock.Once cured it can be drilled, filed and sawn, it is great for filling holes or screw threads so that you can re-drill and tap to repair the thread. Once mixed it needs to be used within 5 minutes and is fully cured in 3 hours at normal room temperature.

Title: ToolkitRC M7AC (US Plug) 1~6S 15A 300W AC/DC Multifunction Balance Charger/Discharger
Description: The ToolkitRC M7AC is a versatile, multifunction tool that integrates functions such as charging, discharging, cycling, signal test/signal source (PWM/PPM/SBUS), multimeter, smart consumer-grade drone battery charging, customizable multi-language voice alerts, and so much more. The M7AC is lightweight, and compact, and it has a built-in power supply so that it can operate from a 100~240V AC mains power source. It also has the ability to operate on a 7~28V DC power supply which is perfect for charging at the flying field, race track, or boating lake.When the M7AC is used with an AC power supply, it is capable of charging at up to 100W, on a DC power supply, it is capable of charging at an impressive 300W. A wide variety of different chemistry batteries can also be charged on the M7AC, these include, LiPo, LiHV, LiFe, Li-ion, and LTO (Lithium-Titanium-Oxide) @ 1~6S, NiMh @ 1~16S, and Pb @ 1~10S.The M7AC is simple and straightforward to use, it has an easy-to-read, wide-angle IPS 2.4"x320x240 pixel full-color LCD screen, simple to use menu scrolling/enter wheel, and an exit/save button. Inputs include an AC and DC socket, and outputs include an XT60 and XT30 charging port, 2~6S balance port, USB port, TF card port, and voice function speaker. When required, the powerful, intelligent, high-flow cooling fan cuts in at half speed when internal temperatures of the charger exceed 45°C, this will then switch to full power when temperatures exceed 53°C.The ToolkitRC M7AC multifunction balance charger/discharger is a must for every modeler's workshop due to its compact size, incredible versatility, its ability to run from AC and DC power sources, and its easy-to-use, user-friendly programming menus.

Title: Turnigy Plush-32 12A (2~4S) Brushless Speed Controller w/BEC (Rev1.1.0)
Description: The Turnigy Plush-32 brushless ESC comes with a 32-bit ARM controller which offers higher resolution, makes it quicker, smoother, and more responsive to your throttle inputs. As you would expect, all the Turnigy Plush-32 are manufactured to the same high-quality standards that you have come to expect with all the Turnigy Plush ESCs.Now with the updated Rev1.1.0 firmware, these speed controllers offer a few more programming options over previous models. These include motor type, spool-up acceleration, PWM frequency, beacon delay, and an adjustable BEC (this is only available on the 150A). Most of these revisions are self-explanatory but the "Beacon Delay" does require an explanation. The "Beacon Delay" is quite a unique function that will cause the ESC to start "beeping" after a predetermined delay of not using the throttle stick, this can be set via the program card. The loud beeping noise is perfect for finding your model if it gets lost in high grass, standing crops, or in the bush, etc. Please note that you can use your existing Plush 32 programming card but you will not be able to access the revised functions unless you purchase the new Rev1.1.0 programming card.Programming your Plush 32 ESC is made very simple if you use the Plush 32 programming card. No more listening to the beeps, and guessing when to move your throttle, the programming card changes settings with the press of a button. Easy-to-read LEDs let you know exactly how your ESC is being programmed and set. So don’t forget to include a programming card when purchasing your ESC, see related products.

Title: Hobbywing QUICRUN WP 1080 G2 80A 2-3S Brushed ESC for 1/10 Crawlers
Description: Hobbywing QUICRUN WP 1080 G2 80A 2-3S Brushed ESC designed specifically for 1/10 crawlers offers a high performance at a low price, it is extremely robust, reliable, and packed full of features. One of the major features which makes it ideal for crawlers is the "real car mode", this mode allows the motor to be switched in real-time. This mode will require a spare channel on your RC system with a 3-position switch. This will then allow you to select "forward with brakes", "forward with reverse and brakes", or "forward and reverse", this feature will provide the user with a unique driving experience like you have never seen before.Other features are real-time drag braking, upgraded temperature control, water/dust-proofing to IP-67 standards, and a strong, powerful adjustable SBEC system. The real-time drag braking force also requires an extra RC channel, this will allow you to adjust the drag brake in real-time as you are driving. The latest design of aluminum heatsink provides much better heat control by reducing the operating temperature by around 15°C for improved reliability, there is also a fan mount if you require for even more cooling in extreme conditions. The IP-67 standard means it's splash-proof, water-proof, and dust-proof under normal use, however, it has not been designed to be permanently immersed in water for any period of time. The SBEC system is adjustable between the following voltages 6~7.4~8.4V, and can deliver 4A continuous current, or a peak current of 6A, more than enough to power most servos on the market including HV types.Setting the 15 separate ESC parameters is very straightforward using the easy-to-use single set button, or the Hobbywing digital LED program card.So, if you are looking for a feature-filled brushed ESC for your 1/10 crawler, then look no further than the cost-effective, compact, reliable, high-performance Hobbywing QUICRUN WP 1080 G2 80A ESC.

Title: Turnigy 4000mAh 4S 30C Lipo Pack w/XT-60
Description: Turnigy batteries are known the world over for performance, reliability, and price. It’s no surprise to us that Turnigy Lipoly packs are the go-to pack for those in the know. Turnigy batteries deliver the full rated capacity at a price everyone can afford.Turnigy batteries are equipped with heavy-duty discharge leads to minimize resistance and sustain high current loads. Turnigy batteries stand up to the punishing extremes of aerobatic flight and RC vehicles. Each pack is equipped with XT-60 connectors and JST-XH style balance connectors. All Turnigy Lipoly battery packs are assembled using IR-matched cells.You won’t find a better deal in Lipoly batteries anywhere!Before making a battery purchase, there are a few things you need to consider. Firstly, what are you powering? The type of hobby vehicle you are powering will determine whether you use a soft battery pack or a Hardcase battery pack. For example, if you’re flying an RCPlaneorMultirotor Drone, you would normally use a soft Lipo pack. However, if you’re using an RCCaraHardcasebattery pack will prevent the battery from being pierced if you crash.Secondly, it's important to know what battery capacity (mAh) you need, the cells count (S), and the optimal discharge rate (C rating). This will also be determined by the vehicle you are using the battery for.

Title: XK (RTF) K200 4ch Flybarless Micro Helicopter w/6-Axis Gyro, Altitude & Position Hold
Description: This amazing micro helicopter is packed with features to make it fun and easy to fly. The flybarless system is controlled and stabilized using a 6-axis gyro system which gives it a stability rarely seen before in a small RC helicopter. The K200 also has a barometric pressure sensor for altitude hold and an optical sensor for position hold. This coupled with the 6-axis gyro, makes it the perfect choice for the novice pilot.The XK K200 has everything you need to get flying, a 2.4Ghz 4ch transmitter with precision metal constructed control stick gimbals, a 7.4V 600mAh 25C LiPo battery, and a USB charging lead. The transmitter has the ability to be easily switched to operate as either Mode 1 or Mode 2, these modes give you the choice of which control functions, are on which control sticks. Another quite unique feature for a small ready-to-fly helicopter is that it can be flown if you wish using a Futaba S-BUS, or a DSM transmitter and receiver. This will appeal to experienced pilots who would like to use their own computer radios to fly the XK K200.Another feature of this great little helicopter which will help beginners immensely is an auto take-off and landing function, at the flick of a switch you can make the helicopter take off to an altitude of about 1.5 meters, or bring it back to a smooth, safe landing. Other features are an incredible flight time of around 16 minutes on one battery charge, a low voltage battery alarm, a powerful 050 carbon brushed motor, and a quick detachable tail motor in the event of crash damage.So, to summarise, this ready-to-fly XK K200 with its 6-axis gyroscopic stabilization system, barometric pressure altitude control, and optical positioning mode, is a must for anyone who wants to learn to fly an RC helicopter the easy way. This coupled with the K200 being manufactured to the highest of standards, with the highest quality components for strength, reliability, and crash resistance, makes this a must-have heli for the novice or experienced pilot.
