Title: Universal 2 Part Epoxy Repair Putty (30g)
Description: A must for every toolbox, this cold setting epoxy putty will repair just about anything. Uses include repairing metals, plastics, wood, glass, ceramics and masonry etc. It comes in with 2 sticks, one has the properties of epoxy resin and one has the properties of the hardner. To use you cut equal quantities off of each stick and knead them together, they have different colors, one being blue and the other yellow, when you have a green color they are mixed properly. The putty is now ready for use, it moulds like ordinary putty but when cured it sets like rock.Once cured it can be drilled, filed and sawn, it is great for filling holes or screw threads so that you can re-drill and tap to repair the thread. Once mixed it needs to be used within 5 minutes and is fully cured in 3 hours at normal room temperature.

Title: GOOSKY (RTF) Mode 2 Legend S2 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter (White)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S2 is a game-changing, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique one-piece concave CNC bracket for the swashplate actuator system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for low-time and experienced pilots alike.This RTF (Ready-to-Fly) version of the Legend S2 is not only supplied with metal-geared servos, flight controller, and battery but a dedicated, simple-to-use GOOSKY T8 transmitter as well. This transmitter is squarely aimed at the novice pilot, with no complicated computer programming, basically just switch it on and fly, but it is also perfect for the more experienced pilot who just wants to get flying quickly and easily. Out of the box, the 2 factory set defaults allow for either a sedate, quiet flying machine on the fully stabilized setting, or flick the Tx flight mode switch into the advanced setting to unleash a wild and exciting 3D aerobatic machine. The transmitter is Mode 2, meaning that the left/right, and fore/aft cyclic are on the right stick, and throttle/tail rotor are on the left stick. The T8 also includes its own 3.7V 18650 2800mAh battery which is easily charged via the Type-C USB port in the side of the transmitter.The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precise control of the two flight modes as mentioned above. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler. The T8 transmitter uses the popular S-FHSS protocol which the GTS system is set up for, however, it can also be matched to a DSMX system if you wish by adding a DSMX-compatible satellite receiver.Other features include a quick-release tail rotor blade system, CNC machined metal parts for reinforcement of the frame, fixed length pushrods for accurate set-up, tough one-piece landing gear, high-strength alloy tail boom, and a unique tail boom holder design to help minimize damage in a crash.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to fly, you just need to charge the battery and away you go. If you need to change the default settings, then this is quick and simple via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S2 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning, tough, and well-engineered helicopter.

Title: Turnigy Plush-32 12A (2~4S) Brushless Speed Controller w/BEC (Rev1.1.0)
Description: The Turnigy Plush-32 brushless ESC comes with a 32-bit ARM controller which offers higher resolution, makes it quicker, smoother, and more responsive to your throttle inputs. As you would expect, all the Turnigy Plush-32 are manufactured to the same high-quality standards that you have come to expect with all the Turnigy Plush ESCs.Now with the updated Rev1.1.0 firmware, these speed controllers offer a few more programming options over previous models. These include motor type, spool-up acceleration, PWM frequency, beacon delay, and an adjustable BEC (this is only available on the 150A). Most of these revisions are self-explanatory but the "Beacon Delay" does require an explanation. The "Beacon Delay" is quite a unique function that will cause the ESC to start "beeping" after a predetermined delay of not using the throttle stick, this can be set via the program card. The loud beeping noise is perfect for finding your model if it gets lost in high grass, standing crops, or in the bush, etc. Please note that you can use your existing Plush 32 programming card but you will not be able to access the revised functions unless you purchase the new Rev1.1.0 programming card.Programming your Plush 32 ESC is made very simple if you use the Plush 32 programming card. No more listening to the beeps, and guessing when to move your throttle, the programming card changes settings with the press of a button. Easy-to-read LEDs let you know exactly how your ESC is being programmed and set. So don’t forget to include a programming card when purchasing your ESC, see related products.

Title: RADIOMASTER BOXER  ELRS 16ch FCC 2.4GHz RC Transmitter w/Open-Source EdgeTX Firmware
Description: The RADIOMASTER BOXER radio has been created to be the best radio in its class without compromising anything. It is supplied with the EdgeTX operating system and a built-in ELRS module (FCC or LBT). There is also an external JR-style module compartment so that you can use all your favorite modules and protocols.The amount of features is too numerous to list, but here is a small selection of the many incredible features of the BOXER radio. Super-smooth high precision 4.0 hall sensor gimbals, adjustable length CNC metal folding stand, compact ergonomic design, oversized battery compartment for large battery packs (batteries not supplied), adjustable, and removable "T" shape antenna, versatile 6-position switch for flight mode access, and so much more. Also included is a high-density, shock-proof padded storage and carry case. This is perfect for keeping your treasured transmitter safe whilst being stored or traveling.As mentioned above, the RADIOMASTER BOXER has the cutting-edge EDGETX software pre-installed. This open-source firmware is highly customizable to allow users to configure their transmitters through the supplied USB-C data port to adjust the settings for their individual preferences and specific needs. EdgeTX supports a wide range of RC protocols and is a versatile and powerful tool which makes it extremely popular with the RC community. RADIOMASTER works closely with the EdgeTX team to develop and optimize the user experience and will continue to ensure that the concept and standards are carried forward into the future. The programming of the transmitter is a very simple affair as well, using a combination of the system/page buttons, and the menu scrolling wheel.Overall this is an easy-to-use, flexible, compact, open-source transmitter that is ergonomically designed, making it comfortable to hold, and it has a string of high-quality features that puts it in a class of its own.

Title: Turnigy Bolt 1000mAh 3S 11.4V 65~130C High Voltage Lipoly Pack (LiHV)
Description: Turnigy Bolt series high voltage lithium polymer batteries are here, ready to bring out the next level of power to your high-performance model. Turnigy Bolt batteries are built to the absolute highest standards to provide competition-level performance. With features such as gold-plated balance leads, silver-plated discharge wires, and a reformulated matrix to allow you to safely charge them up to 4.35 volts per cell! These batteries are simply unmatched by any other in performance and build quality!In addition to the higher nominal and max voltage, they are engineered to take high C rate discharge up to 65C continuous. Basically what this means is that these batteries will provide more power in your machine, especially during high current draw maneuvers, and they will provide a longer cycle life due to the lower operating temperatures of the pack.Top-notch performance and build quality make these packs ideal for high-demand flying such as 3D helicopters, EDFs, F3A, and any other high current draw applications. Each pack is built with heavy-duty flexible silicone wire leads and a pre-installed connector ready to handle all you can throw at it. The great thing about the Turnigy Bolt batteries is that you can charge them with any standard lipo charger for basic use, they will simply perform like a standard pack. When using the proper charger such as our Turnigy Neutron chargers, which are designed with the special protocol for these LiHV batteries, you can unlock the full potential of the Turnigy Bolt batteries.More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY Bolt series lithium polymer batteries are built with a LiCo nano-technology substrate complex and an all-new CNT (carbon nano tube) additive greatly improving power transfer and making the oxidation/reduction reaction more efficient, this helps electrons pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and a higher discharge rate than a similar density lithium polymer (non-nano-tech) battery.LiHV stands for “High Voltage Lithium Polymer”. These batteries have been around for years and can be safely charged to 4.35V, higher than the typical voltage ofLipos.The advantages of LiHV batteries are higher power and longer running times. LiHV batteries can be charged to 4.35V per cell, higher than normal LiPo batteries which sit at 4.20V. For example, a 4S LiHV pack charged at 4.35V would give you 17.4V. Whereas a Lipo battery on the same charge would only get 16.8V. LiHV batteries also have lower internal resistance and are less prone to "puffing".For those that love graphs, it means a straighter, longer curve. For pilots, it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance.Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings, and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, Turnigy Bolt series LiHV packs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!Features:• Higher charge voltage than standard lipos• Super high 65C discharge rate• Perfect for high-performance models• Higher capacity than comparable-size packs• Heavy-duty silicone wire discharge leadsSpecs:Capacity:1000mAhVoltage:3S / 3 Cell / 11.4VDischarge:65C Constant / 130C BurstWeight:94gDimensions:71x33x20mmBalance Plug:JST-XHDischarge Plug:XT60

However, if you’re using an RCCaraHardcasebattery pack will prevent the battery from being pierced if you crash.It's important to know what battery capacity (mAh) you need, the cell count (S), and the optimal discharge rate (C rating). Title: SonicModell (Kit) AR Wing PRO "White Falcon" EPP 1000mm
Description: The SonicModell AR Wing PRO "White Falcon" is a special, all-white version of the popular standard AR Wing PRO. It is still a tough, dynamic, efficient, lifting-body flying wing that delivers an impressive performance with style. The White Falcon features detachable wings, which means the wings can be easily removed for transport. Other features are a large battery/flight controller bay, a nose camera bay for FPV flying that suits DJI and other cameras, and numerous compartments for the FPV transmitter (plenty of room for long-range systems) and your RC receiver, etc. These compartments have aerodynamically designed NACA air cooling systems to keep everything including your FPV gear nice and cool.The aerodynamic design allows for a highly agile, responsive, and precise flying model that gives a sharp reaction to your control inputs. The White Falcon is no slouch in the performance department either, with its included power system it can reach speeds of up to 130km/h. This is very impressive, but its wide speed range means that it is equally happy flying around very slowly as well.This version of the AR Wing PRO "White Falcon" is supplied in kit form, so you will require your own motor, prop, ESC, and servos. The airframe is nicely molded in a tough white EPP foam, complete with molded C of G dimples, and for enhanced stability and crash resistance, there is a strong carbon-fiber wing spar. The bottom of the White Falcon is completely flat with stick-on teflon skids, there is nothing really to catch on the ground when landing (apart from the surface control horns) to cause damage, even the servo horns are recessed. The control surfaces themselves come molded to the wing itself with a foam hinge, but CA hinges are also provided as an option. The control surface side of things is completed with a highly accurate, no-slop ball link system.The SonicModell AR Wing PRO "White Falcon" offers great performance, stacks of room for all your equipment, has an impressive payload of around 900g, is very easy to assemble, and is the perfect package for FPV and pure fun flying.

Title: Turnigy Graphene 2200mAh 3S 45C LiPo Pack w/ XT60
Description: TURNIGY, the name synonymous with performance, reliability, and innovation is excited to release a powerful new battery chemistry in the Turnigy Graphene!What's in it for you? Well not only do Graphene batteries go harder for longer but they're unlike anything you have seen or used before.Turnigy Graphene packs utilize carbon in the battery structure to form a single layer of graphene just 0.335nm thick, making that type of battery substrate the thinnest known to mankind. The graphene particles form a highly dense compound allowingelectrons to flow with less resistance compared to traditional lipoly battery technologies.The result is a battery capable of maintaining greater power output whilst remaining much cooler under load.  Since heat and resistance are batteries' natural enemies, graphene chemistry has significantly reduced these problems and the result is an incredible boost in cycle life.Turnigy Graphene batteries are the new standard for serious hobbyists who require POWER ON DEMAND.Advantages over traditional Lipo batteries.• Power density: 0.15-0.17kw/kg (5Ah-16Ah)• Power density: 0.13-0.15kw/kg (1Ah-4.9Ah).• Stable High pack voltage through duration of use.• High discharge rate, giving more power under load.• Internal impedance can reach as low as 1.2mO compared to that of 3mO of a standard Lipoly.• Greater thermal control, packs stay much cooler under extreme conditions• Higher capacity during heavy discharge.• Maintains higher pack capacity even after hundreds of cycles• Fast charge capable, up to 15C on some batteries.• Longer Cycle Life (reportedly in excess of 900 during testing).
note: Graphene LiPo Batteries only require a standard Lipo battery charger.

Title: Flight Mode Switcher for APM, PX4 and Pix Autopilots

See under the"Files"tab for installation instructions.Once installed on your transmitter and set up in "Mission Planner" it is very simple to use, just press the relevant mode button on the switcher and the model will go into that mode. There is an indicator light to show which mode has been selected and is in use.Features:• Allows the user to easily set 6 flight modes• Simple and straightforward to install• Compact and lightweight• Status indicator lights

Title: PLA Luminous Green 0.5kg 3mm eSUN
Description: HobbyKing is excited to be carrying the full range of the ESUN brand of 3D printing filament. ESUN is recognised as one of the world's leading and most innovative manufacturers for 3D additive printing.The PLA, ABS, Flexible, Luminous and many other types of materials are perfect for whatever application you have in mind. Title: GOOSKY (RTF) Mode 2 Legend S2 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter (Green/Yellow)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S2 is a game-changing, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique one-piece concave CNC bracket for the swashplate actuator system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for low-time and experienced pilots alike.This RTF (Ready-to-Fly) version of the Legend S2 is not only supplied with metal-geared servos, flight controller, and battery but a dedicated, simple-to-use GOOSKY T8 transmitter as well. This transmitter is squarely aimed at the novice pilot, with no complicated computer programming, basically just switch it on and fly, but it is also perfect for the more experienced pilot who just wants to get flying quickly and easily. Out of the box, the 2 factory set defaults allow for either a sedate, quiet flying machine on the fully stabilized setting, or flick the Tx flight mode switch into the advanced setting to unleash a wild and exciting 3D aerobatic machine. The transmitter is Mode 2, meaning that the left/right, and fore/aft cyclic are on the right stick, and throttle/tail rotor are on the left stick. The T8 also includes its own 3.7V 18650 2800mAh battery which is easily charged via the Type-C USB port in the side of the transmitter.The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precise control of the two flight modes as mentioned above. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler. The T8 transmitter uses the popular S-FHSS protocol which the GTS system is set up for, however, it can also be matched to a DSMX system if you wish by adding a DSMX-compatible satellite receiver.Other features include a quick-release tail rotor blade system, CNC machined metal parts for reinforcement of the frame, fixed length pushrods for accurate set-up, tough one-piece landing gear, high-strength alloy tail boom, and a unique tail boom holder design to help minimize damage in a crash.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to fly, you just need to charge the battery and away you go. If you need to change the default settings, then this is quick and simple via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S2 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning, tough, and well-engineered helicopter.

Title: FrSky R9 Mini Long Range Telemetry Receiver w/Ipex4 Dipole Antenna (International Version 915MHz)
Description: The R9 Mini is a compact, lightweight long range 900MHz receiver that is perfect for racing drones. The telemetry feedback coupled with the redundancy function improves the security of the RC link with your model. This receiver has all the features of the previous R9 receivers, super low latency, high precision and ipex antenna connection which allows quick replacement in the event of damage. This version of the R9 is fitted with a "T" type Ipex4 dipole antenna for improved range and interference rejection. The other thing with this antenna is it makes mounting onto a small racing drone so much easier and it is less likely to get damaged in a crash.This receiver is the International version that operates on 915MHz, is S.Port enabled and has an RSSI/SBUS output and up to 16CH's. S.Port (Smart Port) is a signal wire duplex digital transmission interface which has been developed by FrSky and gives a high transmission speed. Suitable for use with the Taranis and Horus range of FrSky transmitters fitted with the 900MHz (R9M) module (see related items). Any other make of transmitter can also be used as long as it can be fitted with the R9M module. With this set up a range of 10km's or more is achievable.A copy of the User Manual is available under the"Files"tab.

Title: RADIOMASTER BOXER MAX (Black) ELRS FCC M2 16ch 2.4GHz RC Transmitter w/Open-Source EdgeTX Firmware
Description: The RADIOMASTER BOXER MAX radio has been created to be the best radio in its class without compromising anything. It is supplied with the EdgeTX operating system, and the ExpressLRS RF system pre-installed (FCC or LBT). There is also an external JR-style module compartment so that you can use all your favorite modules and protocols.The BOXER MAX has to be one of the coolest-looking transmitters on the market. It comes with a simulated carbon-fiber finish as standard and is available with 3 options for the color of the gimbals, and the CNC machined switches, buttons, and roller, etc. These options are red, gold, and black, this one being the stylish black version.The amount of features is too numerous to list, but here is a small selection of the many incredible features of the BOXER MAX. Super-smooth AG01 hall sensor gimbals, adjustable length CNC metal folding stand, comfortable leather grips, compact ergonomic design, oversized battery compartment for large battery packs (batteries not supplied), adjustable, and removable "T" shape antenna, versatile 6-position switch for flight mode access, and so much more. Also included is a high-density, shock-proof padded storage and carry case. This is perfect for keeping your treasured transmitter safe whilst being stored or traveling.As mentioned above, the RADIOMASTER BOXER MAX has the cutting-edge EDGETX software pre-installed. This open-source firmware is highly customizable to allow users to configure their transmitters through the supplied USB-C data port to adjust the settings for their individual preferences and specific needs. EdgeTX supports a wide range of RC protocols and is a versatile and powerful tool which makes it extremely popular with the RC community. RADIOMASTER works closely with the EdgeTX team to develop and optimize the user experience and will continue to ensure that the concept and standards are carried forward into the future. The programming of the transmitter is a very simple affair as well, using a combination of the system/page buttons, and the menu scrolling wheel.Overall this is an easy-to-use, flexible, compact, open-source transmitter that is ergonomically designed, making it comfortable to hold, and it has a string of high-quality features that puts it in a class of its own.

Title: HOTA P6 2 x 300W 1~6S Dual Smart Charger/Discharger (DC Only)
Description: The HOTA range of chargers/dischargers is quickly becoming renowned for their quality, reliability, and numerous great features. This amazing dual charger/discharger can charge up to 2 x 300W all in a tiny package measuring 111x70x45mm and weighing just 292g. It offers loads of protection to safeguard against damaging itself or your battery packs such as temperature protection, capacity protection, input and output reverse protection, short circuit protection, and much more. See the attached user manual for the full list of features and protections.It features a simple system for programming, there is a channel key for selecting which channel you wish to program and a speed shuttle key for all the other programming selections. This speed shuttle key is pressed to enter the task, scrolled to adjust the task, then pressed again to enter the task, all very straightforward and simple. It also has a 2.4" 260000 colors IPS display which makes the whole user experience a very easy and simple operation. A unique feature of this charger is that it recycles the discharge power when being used to discharge a battery. This regenerative discharge takes most of the output battery's energy and puts it back into the input battery in a balanced environmentally friendly way. Another feature of the charger is the advanced circuit design and charging algorithm which ensures better and more reliable charging and discharging.The HOTA H6 Dual has numerous ports, on the input side, there is a standard XT60 DC port for the input power of 10.5~30V DC. Then on the output side, there is a micro (type C) USB port for firmware updates, a multi-function port, 2 x XT60 output ports, 2 x 6S balance ports, and a 5V (type A) USB port. The multi-function port has a Futaba/JR style connector which can be used as a servo tester for testing your servos or for testing the output of your receiver and transmitter.Overall this is a great little user-friendly dual charger/discharger that will charge or discharge 2 batteries simultaneously. It is suitable for LiHV, LiPo, LiFe, LiLon, Lixx, NiZn, NiCd, NiMH, Pb, and Eneloop batteries and each port can charge/discharge different chemistry batteries at the same time. All this can be done in your workshop if you have a suitable power supply or out in the field when connected to a DC battery source.

Title: GOOSKY (RTF) Mode 2 Legend S1 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter (Pink)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S1 is a small, game-changing, high-performance, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique "cage body" metal geared servo system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the designers in producing a tough, easy-to-fly, maintenance-free, high-performance helicopter suitable for entry-level and experienced pilots alike.This RTF (Ready-to-Fly) version of the Legend S1 is supplied not only with the servos, flight controller, 2 batteries, and charger, but a dedicated, simple-to-use GOOSKY T8 transmitter as well. This transmitter is squarely aimed at the beginner, no complicated computer programming, basically just switch on and fly, but it is also perfect for the more experienced pilot who just wants to get flying quickly and easily. The transmitter is Mode 2, meaning that the left/right, and fore/aft cyclic are on the right stick, and throttle/tail rotor are on the left stick. The T8 also includes its own 3.7V 18650 2800mAh battery which is easily charged via the Type-C USB port in the side of the transmitter. The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precision control with two flight modes. Flight mode 1 (switchable from the Tx) is self-stabilization that offers amazing stability for the beginner, and flight mode 2 allows for high-performance aerobatics and full 3D flight. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to fly, you just need to charge one of the batteries and away you go. If you need to change the default settings, then this is quick and simple via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S1 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning little helicopter.Features:• Pre-assembled w/motors, servos, gyro stabilization, and dedicated Mode 2 transmitter• Tough, durable composite frame w/alloy boom• Metal blade grips and swashplate• Unique "cage body" metal geared servo system• Quick change battery system without having to remove the canopy• Easy set up using the GOOSKY mobile phone APP• Supplied with 2 flight batteries and charger
type: GOOSKY (RTF) Mode 2 Legend S1 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter

Title: HobbyKing® ™ Boom Stopper w/Fuse
Description: The Boom Stopper will help stop short circuits from blowing your electronics up. Simply plug in the Boom Stopper between the power source, usually your battery, and the components you are wanting to power for the first time. If there is a problem the inline 2A fuse will blow, instead of your components. When the fuse is blown the LED will light up indicating there is a short circuit and the Boom Stopper will reduce the current to a level that won't immediately damage your electronics, giving you time to remove the power supply.A great way to prevent issues with ESC reverse polarity problems and a must-have tool for new build drones, with their multitude of wires, complex power distribution boards, and numerous ESCs, it's easy to get a component reversed. You can avoid the chance of a costly mistake simply by using the Boom Stopper the first time you power up your project.Oh and just in case you weren't sureDO NOT ATTEMPT TO FLY WITH THE BOOM STOPPER ATTACHED OR START YOUR MOTORS, it is purely to check that you don't have a fault in your wiring. With a 2A fuse, you won't get very far if you do try.
features: ['• Includes LED fuse indicator', '• Current limited to 2A']

Title: FrSky X8R 8/16Ch S.Bus ACCST Telemetry Receiver W/Smart Port (no antenna cover) (EU)
Description: The top of the range, 16 Channel X8R receiver from FrSky with 8 normal PWM outputs and no less than 16 channels on the dedicated S.BUS output. Now supplied with the 2015 firmware to compy with EU regulations.The X8R is a surprisingly compact package compared to many 8 channel receivers and has all of the amazing functionality associated with FrSky products. The Smart Port supports the new hub-less sensors in addition to the older hub analog sensors.The X8R supports 8 standard servo outputs, with a further 8 being available by using the S.Bus line with S.Bus supported servos or use a FrSky S.Bus Decoder, giving you a total of 16 channels. Alternatively, you can use two X8R receivers in combination and the channels will sync 1-8 on the first and 9-16 on the second. The second option will give a fantastic degree of redundancy, essential when flying large models and highly desirable in any event.The X8 protocol is backward compatible, so that in D8 mode it works with the DHT, DJT, DFT and DHT-U transmitter modules. This mode you facilitate a total of 8 channels and all of the Smart Port functions so that you can still use the full range of digital sensors.The PCB antenna has been recorded as providing up to a 20% gain in range over traditional and to save weight, these antennas do not have an external case.This is an outstanding receiver for all applications and is perfect for use with the FrSky Horus, X9D and X9E Taranis transmitters, with their built-in XJT Module or any of the D8 systems to take advantage of the new digital Smart Port sensors.The firmware of the X8R receiver can be upgraded by using the USB upgrade cables available separately (please see related items.)

Description: The Micro Engineering Company was founded in 1964 and over the years has become one of the leading companies in the US manufacturing model railway accessories. They started of producing scale model railway track in a single gauge then expanded this into a long line of track and track accessories in H0, N, G and 0 gauge scales. They then branched out into a wide range of highly detailed injection molded styrene kits including buildings, girder bridges, trackside accessories and much much more.These tall steel viaducts are some of the most spectacular, impressive and interesting bridges on the railways. They are used to span wide and/or steep valleys, often replacing the old wooden trestle bridges. The bridges are beautifully detailed and are often the center piece of the modellers layout. This is an 80ft extension for the H0n3 Tall Steel Viaduct Bridge kit so that you can design and customize the bridge to your own requirements. The kit includes 1 x 30ft span, 1 x 50ft span and 1 x 3 story tower. Detail includes bent and tower cross bracing, cross lacing, gusset plates and extensive rivet detail.The bridges are easy to assemble pre-colored injection molded styrene kits that require assembling and glueing. An illustrated instruction sheet is included to enable you to build the bridge of your dreams for your model railway.

Title: ToolkitRC ST8 Advanced Multiple Servo Tester and Data Analyzer
Description: The ToolkitRC ST8 Advanced Multiple Servo Tester is a servo tester like no other. It has an amazing number of features that are usually reserved for the best professional test equipment. It can run 4 servos independently, or it can control 8 servos from a single input. Servos can be controlled using pre-set control modes, or even more accurately via the manual scroll wheel. Servos can also be driven from an external input signal, with support for PWM, PPM, or SBUS signals.There are various measurement modes available, these allow you to test things like the response speed of servos and current draw. Current draw is a very useful piece of information to have as you can then be sure your BEC system has sufficient power to supply the required servo load. Also, it will show you for example if there is a high current load caused by a sticky control surface or a tight pushrod. All this information is clearly visible on the 2.4" TFT RGB 320x240 resolution LCD display.The ST8 can handle an input voltage of anything from 7~28V, this is connected to the tester via an XT60 socket. The servo tester then powers the servos, and the output voltage can be adjusted from 5~28V to suit standard and high-voltage servos.

Firstly, what are you powering? The type of hobby vehicle you are powering will determine whether you use a soft battery pack or a Hardcase battery pack. For example, if you’re flying an RCPlaneorMultirotor Drone, you would normally use a soft Lipo pack. However, if you’re using an RCCaraHardcasebattery pack will prevent the battery from being pierced if you crash.Secondly, it's important to know what battery capacity (mAh) you need, the cell count (S), and the optimal discharge rate (C rating). This will also be determined by the vehicle you use the battery for.

Title: XK A260 (RTF) F8F Rare Bear 4ch RC Reno Racer w/2.4GHz Tx & 3D/6G Gyro System 380mm
Description: This beautiful model of a Grumman F8F Rare Bear Reno Racer with brushed 1020 motor, and 3D/6G gyro stabilization system not only looks great, but it flies great as well. The built-in switchable 6-axis gyro flight stabilization system makes it perfect for both beginners and experts alike. It is tough too, it's constructed from durable, crash-resistant EPP foam which is light, extremely strong, and ready to take all the knocks and bangs associated with learning to fly.The 3D/6G stabilization system is switchable between beginner mode and 3D mode via a simple push button on the top of the transmitter. In full stabilization mode, the amount of pitch, roll, and yaw is limited, plus it mixes in a small amount of rudder with the ailerons to enable it to perform perfectly coordinated turns, ideal for beginners. In 3D mode, it will allow the F8F Rare Bear to carry out many aerobatic maneuvers such as loops, rolls, and much more. If you have 3D mode selected and get into a muddle whilst flying, a simple press of the button will return the model to the fully stabilized mode and it will return to normal level flight. The supplied transmitter also has an aileron and elevator rates function, once again this is a simple push button that will increase, or decrease the amount of throw of the control surfaces. Also included is a fail-safe system which will prevent any flyaways if the signal is lost between the transmitter and receiver.The model is very quick to assemble and all the necessary tools are supplied in the box, no gluing is required. All the components are screwed together, which makes it perfect if you want to fit it back into its box for transporting, this makes it an ideal companion to take with you on vacation!If you wish to fly the F8F with your own transmitter then the included receiver/gyro board can operate with Futaba S-BUS receivers or any other receivers with S-BUS ports. It will also work with multi-protocol transmitters if the correct protocol is set, details in the user manual.The model is supplied with everything you need to fly out of the box (except Tx batteries) including a 3.7V 400mAh battery, and USB charger.

Title: HobbyKing™ KK2.1HC Multi-Rotor Hard Case Flight Control Board
Description: This is the KK2.1HC without the programmer (sold separate). Perfect for those who already have an HC set and programmer.The next evolution of the rotor revolution is here!! The KK2.1HC (Hard Case) is packing new found power with updated sensors, memory, header pins, hard case and remote programmer.The KK2.1HC is the next big evolution of the first generation KK flight control boards. The KK2.1HC was engineered from the ground up to bring multi-rotor flight to everyone, not just the experts. The remote LCD screen and built in software makes installing and setup easier than ever. The screen and programing buttons have been relocated to a remote plug-in programmer and a hard case installed, this makes the KK extremely durable. The plug in programmer (sold separate) uses the exact same format as the onboard version and can be plugged in at anytime for a quick value change. This new design allows the KK to be installed in frames where access to the onboard buttons and screen was an issue, you can even leave the cable plugged into the KK side and run it out for access to the programmer. The Hard case still retains the standardized 45mm mounting holes and has the buzzer is now internally mounted. Mounting locations and damage to the LCD screen is a thing of the past.A host of multi-rotor craft types are pre-installed, simply select your craft type, check motor layout/propeller direction, calibrate your ESCs and radio and you’re ready to go! All of which is done with easy to follow on screen prompts!The original KK gyro system has been updated to an incredibly sensitive 6050 MPU system, making this the most stable KK board ever and allowing for the addition of an auto-level function. At the heart of the KK2.1HC is an Atmel Mega644PA 8-bit AVR RISC-based microcontroller with 64k of memory. An additional polarity protected header has been added for voltage detection, so no need for on-board soldering. A handy piezo buzzer is also included for audio warning when activating and deactivating the board.The KK2.1HC added polarity protection to the voltage sense header and on-board buzzer. The voltage sense line has been updated for better accuracy. The Hard case is clearly labeled, making installation and connections a snap.If you’re new to multi-rotor flight or have been unsure about how to setup a KK board then the KK2.1HC was built for you. The 6 Pin USBasp AVR programming interface ensures future software updates will be quick and easy.The Mixer Editor allows you to adjust where and how much signal the motors receive from stick input and sensors. This allows you to create any configuration possible with up to 8 motors or servos.

Title: GOOSKY Legend RS4 Flybarless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter Kit w/Motor, Servos & Battery (Yellow)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend RS4 is a powerful 380-class, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, high-power direct-drive main motor, and a belt-driven tail rotor system. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for high-end 3D and aerobatic flying.The Legend RS4 is supplied as an unassembled kit that does require assembly, and it includes a high-performance iron core, hand-wound brushless motor with high-speed bearings and NdFeB magnets, and a 6S (22.2V) 1800mAh 70C LiPo battery. This motor coupled with the supplied 6S battery brings an infinite amount of power for even the most demanding of 3D pilots. Also supplied with the kit are three powerful DS45MG cyclic servos, and one fast DS50MG tail servo. These three cyclic servos, plus the ingenious design of the center structure with built-in bearing alignment bring strength and support to the cyclic control system and provide a precise, fast, and accurate control response.Other features of the Legend RS4 include high-strength aluminum alloy main blade grips, a high-precision tail rotor design with O-ring damping and a unique monorail-guided tail control system, An angled battery compartment for quick battery changes, a strong thick-walled tail boom for stability when performing aggressive 3D flying, and a high strength, lightweight one-piece landing gear.This incredibly powerful 3D helicopter is a must-have for all experienced RC heli pilots, it will deliver thrilling flights, outstanding performance, and unforgettable aerial adventures.

Title: Turnigy Rapid 5000mAh 2S (7.4V) 100C LiPo Battery Pack w/XT90 Connector
Description: Turnigy LiPo battery packs are well known for delivering excellent performance and durability in your favorite RC cars, trucks, boats, and more. The Turnigy Rapid range continues this pedigree using cutting-edge technology to achieve even better performance, greater cycle life, and lower internal resistance. These packs are capable of delivering an incredible discharge rate of 100C!The Turnigy Rapid range of LiPo batteries delivers the power and run time needed for the demanding high-performance models of today. They can deliver a high under-load voltage while retaining reliability even after a high number of cycles. Each cell is precision-matched to each other for its voltage and internal resistance to ensure your battery pack reaches you as evenly matched as possible. The battery is equipped with heavy-duty silicone-covered cabling to minimize resistance and deliver a huge amount of current when you punch the throttle. Each pack also has a heavy-duty connector (see specs) and a JST-XH style balance connector commonly found on all Turnigy batteries.Due to popular demand, we’re expanding the Rapid range to include even more sizes and cell counts in soft pack versions that will fit a wider variety of models in the ever-expanding “basher” market. Best of all, these packs come with an incredible price point!So if you’re looking for incredible value, high-performance batteries for your models, Turnigy Rapid 100C packs are just the ticket!

All Turnigy Lipoly battery packs are assembled using IR-matched cells.You won’t find a better deal on Lipoly batteries anywhere!Before making a battery purchase, there are a few things you need to consider. Firstly, what are you powering? The type of hobby vehicle you are powering will determine whether you use a soft battery pack or a Hardcase battery pack. For example, if you’re flying an RCPlaneorMultirotor Drone, you would normally use a soft Lipo pack. However, if you’re using an RCCaraHardcasebattery pack will prevent the battery from being pierced if you crash.Secondly, it's important to know what battery capacity (mAh) you need, the cell count (S), and the optimal discharge rate (C rating). This will also be determined by the vehicle you use the battery for.

Title: RC ERA C189 (RTF) MD500 US Army Flybarless RC Helicopter w/Tx, Twin Brushless Motors, 6-Axis Gyro & Barometric Altitude Hold
Description: A really nice, ready-to-fly small-scale model of this iconic full-size military helicopter that is full of outstanding features, these make the MD500 not only look great but makes it fly great as well. The MD500 was developed for the military from the Hughes 500 light utility helicopter and became known as the MD500 Defender.The outstanding features of the MD500 include a metal 5-blade flybarless rotor head, twin brushless motors, a 6-axis gyro, and a barometric altitude hold with optional optical positioning. This gives the MD500 incredible stability and an amazing amount of power making it perfect for beginners or the more experienced pilots. In more experienced hands it is capable of all the usual more advanced helicopter maneuvers. Other features include a dedicated transmitter with auto take-off and landing, out-of-control protection (which allows the gyro and stability systems to take over at the flick of a switch), 3 flight modes, a low voltage alarm, and a modular battery design with intelligent power management.This is a great little scale-looking helicopter that is perfect for the beginner due to its advanced aids to help you fly. But it is also very appealing to the more experienced flyers who want a great-looking, maneuverable small helicopter to have some fun with.

TPU98A premium filament is easy to use for high-speed printing on both direct and Bowen style 3D printers. TPU98A filament has exceptionally high heat resistance (138℃) and can be stretched as far as 450% before reaching breaking point. TPU98A filament does not require the use of a heated bed and can even be printed straight onto glass.TPU98A@df works superb with a direct drive feeder, or newer types of Bowden FDM or FFF technology 3D printers. By changing the infill / amount of walls you can create the perception of a higher / lower shore than 98A. TPU98A@df does not require a heated bed to stick well, though you can set it to 0-60°C for extra reassurance.Extremely flexible, the TPU98A filament can be used as vibration dampers, prosthetics or even orthopaedic insoles. Trust our premium TPU98A filament to create the best results every time. An excellent material choice for your next 3D printing project.

GOOSKY (BNF) Legend S2 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter S-FHSS/DSMX (Pink)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S2 is a game-changing, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique one-piece concave CNC bracket for the swashplate actuator system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for low-time and experienced pilots alike.This BNF (Bind-N-Fly) version of the Legend S2 is supplied not only with the servos and flight controller but a built-in S-FHSS protocol, S-BUS/PPM receiver as well. This receiver is compatible with Futaba out of the box, but it can also be used with DSMX systems, this will require a DSMX-compatible satellite receiver (not supplied). The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precision control with two flight modes. Out of the box, the 2 factory set defaults allow for either a sedate, quiet flying machine on the fully stabilized setting, or change into the advanced setting to unleash a wild and exciting 3D aerobatic machine. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler.Other features include a quick-release tail rotor blade system, CNC machined metal parts for reinforcement of the frame, fixed length pushrods for accurate set-up, tough one-piece landing gear, high-strength alloy tail boom, and a unique tail boom holder design to help minimize damage in a crash.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to bind to your own transmitter and is quick and simple to set up via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S2 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning, tough, and well-engineered helicopter.

Description: The Micro Engineering Company was founded in 1964 and over the years has become one of the leading companies in the US manufacturing model railway accessories. Title: H-King (PNF) Avro Lancaster V3 "Dumbo" British WWII Heavy Bomber (1320mm)
Description: Following on from versions 1 and 2 of the H-King Avro Lancaster, this version 3 represents the lightest and most well-mannered version yet.The V3 Lancaster is designed to be the most lightly loaded version of this classic model and therefore the best performing, it is a 'Lightweight, Heavy Bomber', that's hand launch-ready right out of the box. A differential thrust set-up for added yaw control and far more realistic flight performance is the key recommendation to get the very best out of the model, but she'll happily fly on throttle, elevator, and aileron control alone. The V3 Lancaster can now achieve up to 7 minutes flight time on a 1400mAh 3S, but still has the option of an electric retractable undercarriage for those that wish to have it. Weight over the earlier versions has been further saved by removing the opening bomb-bay door mechanism and servo, complete removal of the undercarriage, and removal of the tailwheel steering servo. This lighter weight makes hand launching a simple and trouble-free affair, slow, and realistic scale flight is greatly improved for those low, slow bombing passes, and less power is required meaning greater flight times.The Lancaster was a British WWll heavy bomber that was designed and manufactured by the Avro Company in England. The Lancaster was powered by four Rolls-Royce Merlin engines and first saw service in 1942 and has become one of the most famous aircraft of WW2. It was at the core of RAF's Bomber commands strategic bombing offensive over Europe and it was the main aircraft for the night-time bombing campaigns that followed. The HobbyKing V3 has been finished in a new, authentic color scheme which depicts 619 Squadrons "Dumbo" PG-D aircraft that operated from RAF Strubby, Lincolnshire, during 1943-45.The fully molded EPO foam "Plug N Fly" Lancaster V3 comes pre-painted with scale panel lines, the decals are factory applied, motors and ESC's are pre-wired and installed, the elevator and aileron servos are also pre-installed. Assembly is very straightforward, the canopy, gun turrets, and .303 machine guns need to be fitted, servo pushrods installed, and the tailplane needs gluing in place. Scale 3 blade propellers with spinners and molded cowlings finish off the Lancaster's stunning scale detail which makes this a practical, must-have model for any scale or warbird enthusiast. Battery and radio access is very easy through the bomb-bay doors and these are held closed while flying with some strong permanent magnets. The two-piece wing simply slides onto the wing joining spars and is held in place with two screws. However at 1320mm, the Lancaster is very easy to transport in one piece, so if you wish, the wing can be glued in place too for extra security.

Title: Turnigy Graphene 5000mAh 4S 45C Lipo Pack w/XT90
Description: TURNIGY, the name synonymous with performance, reliability, and innovation is excited to release a powerful new battery chemistry in the Turnigy Graphene!What does this really mean for you? Well not only do Graphene batteries go harder for longer but they're unlike anything you have seen or used before.Turnigy Graphene packs utilize carbon in the battery structure to form a single layer of graphene just 0.335nm thick, making that type of battery substrate the thinnest known to mankind. The graphene particles form a highly dense compound allowing electrons to flow with less resistance compared to traditional Lipoly battery technologies.The result is a battery capable of maintaining greater power output whilst remaining much cooler under load.  Since heat and resistance are the natural enemies of batteries Graphene chemistry has significantly reduced these problems and the result is an incredible boost in cycle life.Turnigy Graphene batteries are the new standard for serious hobbyists who require POWER ON DEMAND.Advantages over traditional Lipo batteries.• Power density: 0.15-0.17kw/kg (5Ah-16Ah)• Power density: 0.13-0.15kw/kg (1Ah-4.9Ah).• Stable High pack voltage through duration of use.• High discharge rate, giving more power under load.• Internal impedance can reach as low as 1.2mO compared to that of 3mO of a standard Lipoly.• Greater thermal control, packs stay much cooler under extreme conditions• Higher capacity during heavy discharge.• Maintains higher pack capacity even after hundreds of cycles• Fast charge capable, up to 15C on some batteries.• Longer Cycle Life 600+

Title: DYS Rhino RM-S12 1470KV High Torque BLDC Brushless Motor for 1/10-1/12 RC Rock Crawlers
Description: The Rhino RM-S12 BLDC series of brushless motors have been designed specifically for competitive 1/10, and 1/12 RC rock crawlers due to having higher controllability and starting torque. They have a hollow stainless steel shaft, and a 14-pole, 12-slot high-torque stator, currently one of the smallest stators on the market today (only 28x12mm). This in conjunction with the specially customized dual tile super strong magnetic design makes them a light, efficient, and extremely powerful crawler motor.The front and rear parts of the motor are CNC machined from high grade 7075 aluminum, the motor windings are high purity copper, and for durability and lower resistance, sealed high-quality, high-precision bearings are used throughout. Installing the RM-S12 to a range of different crawlers is also not a problem, there are multiple M3 tapped threads in the end bell to suit all sorts of vehicle motor mounting.To bring the best out of this motor and to give you the ultimate driving experience with your crawler, we recommend that you match it will the feature-filled Rhino VE40A electronic speed controller (see related products).

Description: A really nice, ready-to-fly small-scale model of this iconic full-size military helicopter that is full of outstanding features, these make the MD500 not only look great but makes it fly great as well. This gives the MD500 incredible stability and an amazing amount of power making it perfect for beginners or the more experienced pilots. In more experienced hands it is capable of all the usual more advanced helicopter maneuvers. Other features include a dedicated transmitter with auto take-off and landing, out-of-control protection (which allows the gyro and stability systems to take over at the flick of a switch), 3 flight modes, a low voltage alarm, and a modular battery design with intelligent power management.This is a great little scale-looking helicopter that is perfect for the beginner due to its advanced aids to help you fly. But it is also very appealing to the more experienced flyers who want a great-looking, maneuverable small helicopter to have some fun with.

Firstly, what are you powering? The type of hobby vehicle you are powering will determine whether you use a soft battery pack or a Hardcase battery pack. For example, if you’re flying an RCPlaneorMultirotor Drone, you would normally use a soft Lipo pack. However, if you’re using an RCCaraHardcasebattery pack will prevent the battery from being pierced if you crash.Secondly, it's important to know what battery capacity (mAh) you need, the cell count (S), and the optimal discharge rate (C rating). Title: Turnigy Plush-32 80A (2~6S) Brushless Speed Controller w/BEC (Rev1.1.0)
Description: The Turnigy Plush-32 brushless ESC comes with a 32-bit ARM controller which offers higher resolution, makes it quicker, smoother, and more responsive to your throttle inputs. As you would expect, all the Turnigy Plush-32 are manufactured to the same high-quality standards that you have come to expect with all the Turnigy Plush ESCs.Now with the updated Rev1.1.0 firmware, these speed controllers offer a few more programming options over previous models. These include motor type, spool-up acceleration, PWM frequency, beacon delay, and an adjustable BEC (this is only available on the 150A). Most of these revisions are self-explanatory but the "Beacon Delay" does require an explanation. The "Beacon Delay" is quite a unique function that will cause the ESC to start "beeping" after a predetermined delay of not using the throttle stick, this can be set via the program card. The loud beeping noise is perfect for finding your model if it gets lost in high grass, standing crops, or in the bush, etc. Please note that you can use your existing Plush 32 programming card but you will not be able to access the revised functions unless you purchase the new Rev1.1.0 programming card.Programming your Plush 32 ESC is made very simple if you use the Plush 32 programming card. No more listening to the beeps, and guessing when to move your throttle, the programming card changes settings with the press of a button. Easy-to-read LEDs let you know exactly how your ESC is being programmed and set. So don’t forget to include a programming card when purchasing your ESC, see related products.

Title: Turnigy nano-tech 5000mah 6S 45C Lipo Pack w/XT-90
Description: More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. Utilising an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and a higher discharge rates than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) batteries.For those that love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves and excellent performance. For pilots it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!!Lithium Polymer batteries are used in many RC hobby industries. Over the last few years, Lipo batteries have become the most popular battery choice for anyone looking for a longer run time and higher power.Lipo batteries weigh less and can be made into almost any size or shape. Lipo batteries have higher capacities, hold more power and have a higher discharge rate, meaning they pack more punch. For safe use and storage of Lipo batteries, you need to follow the rules and treat the batteries with the respect they deserve.The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

More than 90% at 100% C rate.', '• Fast charge capable, up to 15C on some batteries.', '• Longer Cycle Life, almost double that of standard lipoly technology.']

Title: GOOSKY (BNF) Legend S2 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter S-FHSS/DSMX (Pink)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S2 is a game-changing, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique one-piece concave CNC bracket for the swashplate actuator system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for low-time and experienced pilots alike.This BNF (Bind-N-Fly) version of the Legend S2 is supplied not only with the servos and flight controller but a built-in S-FHSS protocol, S-BUS/PPM receiver as well. This receiver is compatible with Futaba out of the box, but it can also be used with DSMX systems, this will require a DSMX-compatible satellite receiver (not supplied). The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precision control with two flight modes. Out of the box, the 2 factory set defaults allow for either a sedate, quiet flying machine on the fully stabilized setting, or change into the advanced setting to unleash a wild and exciting 3D aerobatic machine. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler.Other features include a quick-release tail rotor blade system, CNC machined metal parts for reinforcement of the frame, fixed length pushrods for accurate set-up, tough one-piece landing gear, high-strength alloy tail boom, and a unique tail boom holder design to help minimize damage in a crash.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to bind to your own transmitter and is quick and simple to set up via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S2 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning, tough, and well-engineered helicopter.

Description: The Micro Engineering Company was founded in 1964 and over the years has become one of the leading companies in the US manufacturing model railway accessories. They started of producing scale model railway track in a single gauge then expanded this into a long line of track and track accessories in HO, N, G and O gauge scales. Title: H-King (PNF) Avro Lancaster V3 "Dumbo" British WWII Heavy Bomber (1320mm)
Description: Following on from versions 1 and 2 of the H-King Avro Lancaster, this version 3 represents the lightest and most well-mannered version yet.The V3 Lancaster is designed to be the most lightly loaded version of this classic model and therefore the best performing, it is a 'Lightweight, Heavy Bomber', that's hand launch-ready right out of the box. A differential thrust set-up for added yaw control and far more realistic flight performance is the key recommendation to get the very best out of the model, but she'll happily fly on throttle, elevator, and aileron control alone. The V3 Lancaster can now achieve up to 7 minutes flight time on a 1400mAh 3S, but still has the option of an electric retractable undercarriage for those that wish to have it. Weight over the earlier versions has been further saved by removing the opening bomb-bay door mechanism and servo, complete removal of the undercarriage, and removal of the tailwheel steering servo. This lighter weight makes hand launching a simple and trouble-free affair, slow, and realistic scale flight is greatly improved for those low, slow bombing passes, and less power is required meaning greater flight times.The Lancaster was a British WWll heavy bomber that was designed and manufactured by the Avro Company in England. The Lancaster was powered by four Rolls-Royce Merlin engines and first saw service in 1942 and has become one of the most famous aircraft of WW2. It was at the core of RAF's Bomber commands strategic bombing offensive over Europe and it was the main aircraft for the night-time bombing campaigns that followed. The HobbyKing V3 has been finished in a new, authentic color scheme which depicts 619 Squadrons "Dumbo" PG-D aircraft that operated from RAF Strubby, Lincolnshire, during 1943-45.The fully molded EPO foam "Plug N Fly" Lancaster V3 comes pre-painted with scale panel lines, the decals are factory applied, motors and ESC's are pre-wired and installed, the elevator and aileron servos are also pre-installed. Assembly is very straightforward, the canopy, gun turrets, and .303 machine guns need to be fitted, servo pushrods installed, and the tailplane needs gluing in place. Scale 3 blade propellers with spinners and molded cowlings finish off the Lancaster's stunning scale detail which makes this a practical, must-have model for any scale or warbird enthusiast. Battery and radio access is very easy through the bomb-bay doors and these are held closed while flying with some strong permanent magnets. The two-piece wing simply slides onto the wing joining spars and is held in place with two screws. However at 1320mm, the Lancaster is very easy to transport in one piece, so if you wish, the wing can be glued in place too for extra security.

Title: Turnigy nano-tech 5000mah 6S 45C Lipo Pack w/XT-90
Description: More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. Utilising an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and a higher discharge rates than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) batteries.For those that love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves and excellent performance. For pilots it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!!Lithium Polymer batteries are used in many RC hobby industries. Over the last few years, Lipo batteries have become the most popular battery choice for anyone looking for a longer run time and higher power.Lipo batteries weigh less and can be made into almost any size or shape. Lipo batteries have higher capacities, hold more power and have a higher discharge rate, meaning they pack more punch. For safe use and storage of Lipo batteries, you need to follow the rules and treat the batteries with the respect they deserve.The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

More than 90% at 100% C rate.', '• Fast charge capable, up to 15C on some batteries.', '• Longer Cycle Life, almost double that of standard lipoly technology.']

Title: GOOSKY (RTF) Mode 1 Legend S2 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter (White)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S2 is a game-changing, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique one-piece concave CNC bracket for the swashplate actuator system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for low-time and experienced pilots alike.This RTF (Ready-to-Fly) version of the Legend S2 is not only supplied with metal-geared servos, flight controller, and battery but a dedicated, simple-to-use GOOSKY T8 transmitter as well. This transmitter is squarely aimed at the novice pilot, with no complicated computer programming, basically just switch it on and fly, but it is also perfect for the more experienced pilot who just wants to get flying quickly and easily. Out of the box, the 2 factory set defaults allow for either a sedate, quiet flying machine on the fully stabilized setting, or flick the Tx flight mode switch into the advanced setting to unleash a wild and exciting 3D aerobatic machine. The transmitter is Mode 1, meaning that the throttle and left/right cyclic are on the right stick, and fore/aft cyclic and tail rotor are on the left stick. The T8 also includes its own 3.7V 18650 2800mAh battery which is easily charged via the Type-C USB port in the side of the transmitter.The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precise control of the two flight modes as mentioned above. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler. The T8 transmitter uses the popular S-FHSS protocol which the GTS system is set up for, however, it can also be matched to a DSMX system if you wish by adding a DSMX-compatible satellite receiver.Other features include a quick-release tail rotor blade system, CNC machined metal parts for reinforcement of the frame, fixed length pushrods for accurate set-up, tough one-piece landing gear, high-strength alloy tail boom, and a unique tail boom holder design to help minimize damage in a crash.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to fly, you just need to charge the battery and away you go. If you need to change the default settings, then this is quick and simple via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S2 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning, tough, and well-engineered helicopter.

Description: The FrSky Taranis Q X7S is the next step on from the original Taranis Q X7 and comes in a stunning blue case. It also keeps all the cool features of the Taranis Q X7 but adds even more stunning features. It still has all the usual Taranis features in this radio such as Receiver Signal Strength Indicator (RSSI) alerts, Real-time Flight Data Logging and receiver matching.There is the new ball bearing Hall Sensor M7 gimbals for precision movement of the sticks. It is up to you to determine what flying mode to set the radio to and also if you want self-centering spring-loaded sticks (standard) or the usual stationary set throttle.The Taranis mixes the power of the “OPEN TX” open-source software with upgraded 6 programmable switches (4 x 3-position, 1 x 2-position, 1 x momentary) and two twist knobs. This is great for setting up your switches and controls just how you want them. Using the MicroSD card slot you have unlimited model memory options and you can copy and use all your existing model files from the older TARANIS X9D/X9D Plus/X9E/X7 making it easy to get the new system up and working.The X7S also has a USB port for upgrades and to connect to a PC for settings adjustments. Using the wheel and center enter button makes navigating the backlit menu easy and precise. There is an audio jack output and trainer port. A new addition to the Taranis Q X7S is the wireless trainer function and it is compatible with FrSky Freelink to monitor the sensor data during the flight.Alerts can be presented in the form of audio speech outputs, sound or vibration alerts making this extremely user-friendly. The module bay can be used for JR-type modules with other protocol receivers and also for the use of a FrSky XJT module.The FrSky Taranis Q X7S is a lightweight, reliable, very versatile radio system that is very cost effective.

Title: Turnigy 4000mAh 6S 30C Lipo Pack w/XT90
Description: Turnigy batteries are known the world over for performance, reliability, and price. It’s no surprise to us that Turnigy Lipoly packs are the go-to pack for those in the know. The Turnigy Heavy Duty Series have the amp draw capability you want for your high-performance models at a price everyone can afford.Turnigy batteries are equipped with heavy-duty discharge leads to minimize resistance and sustain high current loads. All Turnigy Lipoly battery packs are assembled using IR-matched cells.You won’t find a better deal in Lipoly batteries anywhere!Before making a battery purchase, there are a few things you need to consider. Firstly, what are you powering? The type of hobby vehicle you are powering will determine whether you use a soft battery pack or a Hardcase battery pack. For example, if you’re flying an RC Plane or Multirotor Drone, you would normally use a soft Lipo pack. However, if you’re using an RC Car a Hardcase battery pack will prevent the battery from being pierced if you crash.Secondly, it's important to know what battery capacity (mAh) you need, the cell count (S), and the optimal discharge rate (C rating). This will also be determined by the vehicle you are using the battery for.

Title: 1/16 (RTR) 4WD Ford Focus w/Brushless Motor, ESP System & Optional Tire Sets
Description: This great-looking iconic 1/16 Ford Focus rally car is supplied complete with a fully proportional 2.4Ghz RC system, lithium battery, USB charger, functioning Tx controlled lights, two extra sets of wheels, and an amazing electronic stability program (ESP) system.This brilliant little car is packed full of features, and one of the most incredible on a vehicle of this size is the ESP system. This gyro-controlled system is adjustable from high gain to low gain using the transmitter. This system helps keep the car going in a rock-steady straight line and improves the handling immensely when driving at high speeds. Other features are the powerful brushless motor setup, which can power the car from a standing start, up to blistering speeds in nanoseconds.Four-wheel drive comes as standard, and so does independent suspension with shock absorbers on all wheels. Other features are Tx-operated independently controlled front and rear lights, oil-filled front and rear differentials, and tough front and rear bumpers for protection. To add to the fun of this amazing little car, two extra sets of wheels and tires are also supplied. Included on the car are a set of standard scale tread tires, then you also get a set of knobbly tires for off-road bashing, and a set of smooth tires for indoor drifting. All these tires are supplied trued and glued to a set of wheels so that they can be changed over extremely quickly when you want to drive on different road surfaces.All in all, this budget-priced, fast, fun-filled, and amazing little ready-to-run brushless RC car with a whole host of features, is a must for all the family and any RC garage.

Title: OrangeRx R617XL cPPM DSM2/DSMX Compatible 6ch Receiver
Description: The OrangeRx 6ch compact receiver has been designed for FPV racing drones with carbon frames. The extra-length antenna allows you to route them outside of the frame for extended range and a robust link to your transmitter.OrangeRx receivers are built using original components, 32-bit MCUs, and with state of the art SMT automation to ensure a quality product each and every time. Every single receiver is manufactured using impedance-controlled PCBs with exact tuning to provide signal stability and range that exceeds any of the previous generation ORX products. In fact, our testing has shown that the R617XL exceeds the range of other receivers in the same class.All R617XL OrangeRx receivers are QC tested using our latest method that ensures range checking takes place as the receiver is programmed. Simply put, if the R617XL cannot pass the range check it cannot be programmed, this ensures 100% of R617XLs are guaranteed to work flawlessly. The R617XL ushers in a new era of quality, reliability, and performance for the OrangeRx lineup.The receiver features "True Diversity" technology, which is especially important for long-range flights and in situations where you need that more robust reception. This receiver is very useful where carbon is used in the construction of your model where the antenna can be in the shadow of the airframe. If one of the antennae cannot receive a signal due to its orientation then the satellite will use the other one to receive the commands from the transmitter.The R617XL has a 6-channel cPPM output allowing for a single line connection with compatible devices. Description: HobbyKing is excited to be carrying the full range of the eSUN brand of 3D printing filament. eSUN is recognised as one of the world's leading and most innovative manufacturers of 3D printing materials.The eSUN PVA 3D print filament is an enviromentally friendly, non toxic, biodegradable and water soluble polymer material. Title: Turnigy nano-tech 850mah 2S 25~40C Lipo Pack w/ JST Connectors
Description: More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious peformance in mind. Utilising an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and a higher discharge rates than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) batteries.For those who love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves and excellent performance. For pilots it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

There are dual omnidirectional antennas to ensure you have the best, stable signal even at longer ranges.Setup is simple with an easy to understand touch screen interface combined with FLYSKYOS. The screen is a 320x480 capacitive color touch screen. There are multiple switches (rotary, slide, 2-position and 3-position) that you can configure just the way you want and with 18 channels you should be able to set up any configuration you need.The Paladin comes with adjustable, high-precision Hall gimbals that can be easily set up for the four different modes of operation.
