Title: Aerostar 20A RVS G2 32bit (2~4S) Electronic Speed Controller w/Reverse Function & 4A 5~6V SBEC
Description: The Aerostar RVS G2 next-generation range of brushless speed controllers moves up a notch from the ground-breaking original Aerostar RVS ESCs. They are more compact, lighter, and process faster due to high-performance 32bit technology, have improved functionality and programmable features, and an upgraded, high-amp SBEC system. New generation MOSFETs ensure that the ESC stays within operating temperatures, and can also safely handle the peak current draw specified. Our RVS (reverse function system) is now instantaneous, with no need for the motor to stop turning, this makes it perfect for EDF braking (reverse thrust), and waterplanes for taxiing, etc. If you don't require the reverse function, simply do not connect the second lead to your receiver, it will then operate as a standard ESC.The Aerostar RVS G2 brushless reversing speed controllers have been designed for a range of fixed-wing applications including as mentioned above, EDF braking (reverse thrust), floatplane/flying boat operations, and with the soft-start function, geared motors using large standard or folding propellers. Another feature of the G2 range of ESC is the addition of HEF (Higher-Efficiency Function) technology. The HEF circuitry allows for better heat dissipation, and lower energy loss when used with certain applications, this function when selected is very similar to "Active Freewheeling". When set to "Off" (the factory default) it's perfect for low to medium KV outrunner motors, when set to "On", it's perfect for high KV outrunners, and inrunners such as those used in EDFs or direct drive racing models.Features that have been retained from the original version are the super smooth start-up, linear throttle response, and multiple protection features. These protections include start-up (prevents motor accidentally starting when powering up), low-voltage cut-off, phase loss, and signal loss, to fully protect the components of your ESC. Programming the many functions of the Aerostar RVS G2 ESC is very simple using either your transmitter or the optional LCD programming card.Installation is very straightforward as these speed controllers come "Plug N Play", no soldering is required as they are supplied pre-fitted with an XT60 connector for the battery, and 3.5mm gold connectors for the motor.

Description: The Dancing Wings Hobby Edge 540 is a large lightweight profile-style foam kit that is quick and simple to build. The full-size Edge 540 is a highly aerobatic airplane with an incredible roll rate of 420° per second and a climb rate of around 3,700ft per minute. The model builds up quickly into a good-looking, fun-to-fly lightweight sport 3D plane that is perfect for park flying and on playing fields.

Description: Get an unfair advantage with Turnigy Nano-tech Airsoft Packs!On the battlefeild, no one wants to compromise on fire power! Title: GOOSKY (RTF) Mode 1 Legend S2 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter (Green/Yellow)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S2 is a game-changing, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique one-piece concave CNC bracket for the swashplate actuator system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for low-time and experienced pilots alike.This RTF (Ready-to-Fly) version of the Legend S2 is not only supplied with metal-geared servos, flight controller, and battery but a dedicated, simple-to-use GOOSKY T8 transmitter as well. This transmitter is squarely aimed at the novice pilot, with no complicated computer programming, basically just switch it on and fly, but it is also perfect for the more experienced pilot who just wants to get flying quickly and easily. Out of the box, the 2 factory set defaults allow for either a sedate, quiet flying machine on the fully stabilized setting, or flick the Tx flight mode switch into the advanced setting to unleash a wild and exciting 3D aerobatic machine. The transmitter is Mode 1, meaning that the throttle and left/right cyclic are on the right stick, and fore/aft cyclic and tail rotor are on the left stick. The T8 also includes its own 3.7V 18650 2800mAh battery which is easily charged via the Type-C USB port in the side of the transmitter.The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precise control of the two flight modes as mentioned above. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler. The T8 transmitter uses the popular S-FHSS protocol which the GTS system is set up for, however, it can also be matched to a DSMX system if you wish by adding a DSMX-compatible satellite receiver.Other features include a quick-release tail rotor blade system, CNC machined metal parts for reinforcement of the frame, fixed length pushrods for accurate set-up, tough one-piece landing gear, high-strength alloy tail boom, and a unique tail boom holder design to help minimize damage in a crash.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to fly, you just need to charge the battery and away you go. If you need to change the default settings, then this is quick and simple via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S2 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning, tough, and well-engineered helicopter.

Title: Turnigy nano-tech 300mAh 2S 35~70C Lipo Pack
Description: More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. Utilizing an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and higher discharge rates than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) batteries.For those who love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves, and excellent performance. For pilots, it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings, and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!The nano-core technology in lithium-ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.
advantages: ['• Power density reaches 7.5 kW/kg.', '• Less Voltage sag during high rate discharge, giving more power under load.', '• Internal impedance can reach as low as 1.2mO compared to that of 3mO of a standard Lipoly.', '• Greater thermal control, pack usually doesn’t exceed 60degC', '• Swelling during heavy load doesn’t exceed 5%, compared to 15% of a normal Lipoly.', '• Higher capacity during heavy discharge. Title: XFLY (PNF) Sukhoi Su-27 Flanker (Grey) w/Twin 50mm 12 Blade EDF Fans & 4S Power System EPO 750mm
Description: The XFLY Sukhoi Su-27 Flanker 750mm EDF jet is an easy-to-fly, great-looking, and versatile scale EDF model that will appeal to a wide variety of pilots, including those with limited experience in flying EDF jets. The 4S-compatible power system includes twin 12-bladed 50mm fan units that deliver an abundance of power for excellent thrust, loads of speed, and an incredible turbine-like sound. The full-size Sukhoi Su-27 Flanker is a long-range air defense jet fighter that was designed as a direct competitor to the McDonnell Douglas F-14. The swept-back wing configuration gives the Su-27 excellent slow-speed handling and short-field capabilities, but it also allows for high maneuverability at speed. These design attributes carry over extremely well to the XFLY model of the Sukhoi Su-27.The XFLY Su-27 is supplied in a "Plug-N-Fly" format meaning that it not only includes the fan units, motors, and ESCs, but 5 x 9g digital servos as well, all you need to supply is a transmitter, receiver, and a 4S (14.8V) 2200~3000mAh LiPo battery. The strong landing gear supplied is fixed with a steerable nose gear, but due to the very stable flight characteristics of the Su-27, it is quite happy being hand-launched with the landing gear removed. This takes it to the next level with even more speed and an almost unlimited vertical performance.The model is made from very tough EPO foam and is beautifully finished in a grey color scheme of the Soviet Air Force. Assembly is quick and simple, there is a small amount of gluing to do on the tail components, but the rest is simply screwed together.So if you are after a scale EDF jet that looks great, flies great, is smooth and stable in flight, and has excellent handling qualities, then the XFLY Sukhoi Su-27 is for you.

Title: Turnigy nano-tech 300mah 1S 45~90C Lipo Pack (Fits Nine Eagles Solo-Pro 100)
Description: The Turnigy nano-tech round single series cells are the perfect solution for many applications where space and weight are at a premium. These round Lipoly cells can be soldered together to make custom packs to suit your needs.More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. Utilizing an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and a higher discharge rate than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) batteries.For those that love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves and excellent performance. For pilots it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!This particular battery has a 2-pin Molex connector. Please refer to the attached image as this Battery has the "B" plug polarity. Please make sure this battery suites your connection. The wrong polarity will damage your electronics.The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity. These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels.This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

Title: Hobbywing QUICRUN-WP 8BL150 G2 Sensorless Brushless ESC for 1/8 Trucks & Monster Trucks
Description: The Hobbywing QUICRUN WP range of ESCs is suitable for the harshest of environments when racing or bashing due to its exceptional water-proof and dust-proof design. This protection level is up to IP-67 standards, which means it is splash-proof, water-proof, and dust-proof under normal use, it has not been designed to be permanently immersed in water for any period of time. The G2 version offers innovative intelligent freewheeling technology, is highly efficient, operates at a lower temperature for improved reliability, and has an upgraded BEC system suitable for HV servos. This upgraded BEC system is adjustable from 6-7.4V, with a continuous current of 6A, and an amazing maximum burst current of 12A.The PCB of the 8BL150 G2 is covered with a patented copper, heat conduction bus bar which helps facilitate rapid heat conduction. This coupled with the highly reliable cooling fan system ensures that the ESC is always kept at an optimum safe operating temperature. The electronic on/off switch has also been upgraded, it is now more durable to resist impact and corrosion damage, and accidental shutdowns are no longer an issue. Other features include a very effective capacitor overheat system that prevents ESC damage, and a built-in 2040uF capacitor module, which eliminates the need for cumbersome external capacitors.With its rugged durability and cutting-edge features, the QUICRUN-WP 8BL150 G2 is ready to take on the most demanding of conditions and is perfect for vehicles such as 1/8 cars, trucks, monster trucks, and off-road buggies.

Title: Dancing Wings Hobby (ARF) Vogee-16 1600mm EP Balsa High-Wing Trainer w/Motor, ESC, Prop & Servos
Description: We have all had to start learning to fly an RC model at some point, and a stable, high-wing trainer that is very forgiving is what is required. The Dancing Wings Hobby Vogee-16 Trainer is the perfect choice for the rookie pilot. It has a large, flat-bottomed wing with dihedral which enables it to fly very slowly, and it has the stability to sort itself out if you get in a muddle. The Vogee's flying characteristics are very benign, beginners tend to over-control, and the Vogee is very gentle in its handling, especially if you install one of the readily available 3-axis gyros that are available on the market these days. It also has a tricycle landing gear with a steerable nosewheel which really helps with the take-offs and landings.The kit comes almost ready to fly and is constructed in balsa for a strong, lightweight, structure that has been factory-covered in an eye-catching, easy-to-see bright color scheme. The versatility of the Vogee-16 means that it can be powered by either an electric or a GP (gas/nitro) setup. This version of the Vogee is supplied with a powerful 2817-900KV brushless motor, a 60A brushless ESC, an 11" prop, 2 x 37g servos, and 2 x 17g servos.The Dancings Wings Hobby Vogee-16 is a very straightforward build and is easily assembled by those with very little experience. You will need to supply your own transmitter, receiver, and battery, and you will also require some tools and glue to complete the model.

Title: Turnigy Nano-Tech 850mAh 3S 30C Lipo Pack
Description: More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. Utilising an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and higher discharge rates than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) batteries.For those that love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves and excellent performance. For pilots, it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultrastrong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. By improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

Title: XK A280 (RTF) P-51D Mustang 4ch RC WW2 Fighter w/2.4GHz Tx, Brushless Motor & 3D/6G Gyro System 560mm
Description: This beautiful scale model of a North American P-51D Mustang WW2 fighter plane with brushless motor, working LED lights, and 3D/6G gyro stabilization system not only looks fantastic, but it flies superbly as well. The built-in switchable 6-axis gyro flight stabilization system makes it perfect for both beginners and experts alike. It is tough too, it's constructed from durable, crash-resistant EPP foam which is light, extremely strong, and ready to take all the knocks and bangs associated with learning to fly.The 3D/6G stabilization system is switchable between beginner mode and 3D mode via a simple push button on the top of the transmitter. In full stabilization mode, the amount of pitch, roll, and yaw is limited, plus it mixes in a small amount of rudder with the ailerons to enable it to perform perfectly coordinated turns, ideal for beginners. In 3D mode, it will allow the P-51D to carry out a whole host of aerobatic maneuvers such as rolls, loops, inverted flight, and so much more. If you have 3D mode selected and get into a muddle whilst flying, a simple press of the button will return the model to the fully stabilized mode and it will return to normal level flight. The supplied transmitter also has an aileron and elevator rates function, once again this is a simple push button that will increase, or decrease the amount of throw of the control surfaces. Also included is a fail-safe system which will prevent any flyaways if the signal is lost between the transmitter and receiver. The very bright LED lights are also controlled from the transmitter, modes include on, flashing, and off, these really add realism to your P-51D.The model is very quick to assemble and all the necessary tools are supplied in the box, no gluing is required. All the components are screwed together, which makes it perfect if you want to fit it back into its box for transporting, this makes it an ideal companion to take with you on vacation!If you wish to fly the P-51D with your own transmitter then the included receiver/gyro board can operate with Futaba S-BUS receivers or any other receivers with S-BUS ports. It will also work with multi-protocol transmitters if the correct protocol is set, details in the user manual.The model is supplied with everything you need to fly out of the box (except Tx batteries) including a spare propeller and spinner, a 7.4V 600mAh battery, and a USB balance charger.

Title: Turnigy Plush-32 40A (2~6S) Brushless Speed Controller w/BEC (Rev1.1.0)
Description: The Turnigy Plush-32 brushless ESC comes with a 32-bit ARM controller which offers higher resolution, makes it quicker, smoother, and more responsive to your throttle inputs. As you would expect, all the Turnigy Plush-32 are manufactured to the same high-quality standards that you have come to expect with all the Turnigy Plush ESCs.Now with the updated Rev1.1.0 firmware, these speed controllers offer a few more programming options over previous models. These include motor type, spool-up acceleration, PWM frequency, beacon delay, and an adjustable BEC (this is only available on the 150A). Most of these revisions are self-explanatory but the "Beacon Delay" does require an explanation. The "Beacon Delay" is quite a unique function that will cause the ESC to start "beeping" after a predetermined delay of not using the throttle stick, this can be set via the program card. The loud beeping noise is perfect for finding your model if it gets lost in high grass, standing crops, or in the bush, etc. Please note that you can use your existing Plush 32 programming card but you will not be able to access the revised functions unless you purchase the new Rev1.1.0 programming card.Programming your Plush 32 ESC is made very simple if you use the Plush 32 programming card. No more listening to the beeps, and guessing when to move your throttle, the programming card changes settings with the press of a button. Easy-to-read LEDs let you know exactly how your ESC is being programmed and set. So don’t forget to include a programming card when purchasing your ESC, see related products.

Title: Turnigy nano-tech 2200mah 3S 35~70C Lipo Pack
Description: Suited to the following models:ALIGN T-REX450, E-flite Blade 450 3D, BEAM E4, MSH Protos Mini, Furion 450, ThunderTiger E325/Mini Titan SE, Caliber 450V, CALIBER 400, RAVE 450, GAUI 330SMore than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious peformance in mind. Utilising an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and a higher discharge rates than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) batteries.For those that love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves and excellent performance. For pilots it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

Title: Insta-Set CA Accelerator 8. oz
ToolkitRC M6D Dual 1~6S 15A 250W DC Balance Charger/Discharger
Description: The ToolkitRC M6D is a versatile dual battery charger that integrates functions such as charging, synchronous charging, discharging, cycling, and smart consumer-grade drone battery charging, it also has a multilingual user interface. The M6D is a DC unit only, so requires an input voltage of 7~28V DC, this makes it perfect for charging at the flying field, race track, or boating lake. For use in the workshop, it can be connected to a mains power supply that can supply the correct DC voltage, and a current of 30A.The M6DAC is capable of charging two batteries at up to 250W each, or, if both channels are used, in the synchronous mode for one battery pack, then it can charge the pack at up to a very impressive 500W. A wide variety of different chemistry batteries can also be charged on the M6D, these include, LiPo, LiHV, LiFe, and Li-ion @ 1~6S, NiMh @ 1~16S, and Pb @ 1~10S.The M6D is simple and straightforward to use, it has an easy-to-read, wide-angle, back-lit, IPS 2.4"x320x240 pixel full-color LCD screen, simple to use metal, menu scrolling/enter wheel, and a ch/exit button. Ports include an XT60 DC input socket, and outputs include 2 x XT60 charging ports, 2 x 2~6S balance ports, a temperature sensor port, and a USB output/upgrade port. When required, the powerful, intelligent, high-flow cooling fan cuts in at half speed when internal temperatures of the charger exceed 45°C, this will then switch to full power when temperatures exceed 53°C.The ToolkitRC M6D dual battery balance charger/discharger is a must for every modeler due to its compact size, incredible charging power, and its easy-to-use, intuitive programming menus.

Title: Turnigy Plush-32 Brushless Speed Controller Programming Card (Rev1.1.0)
Description: The Plush-32 Brushless ESC programming card is designed to make life easy. No more listening to the beeps, and guessing when to move your throttle to make changes to your ESC settings. This programming card changes settings with the press of a button, and easy-to-read LED’s let you know exactly how your ESC has been programmed. This programming card is a must for your Plush-32 series brushless ESC.Now with the updated Rev1.1.0 firmware, this program card offers a few more programming options over previous models. These include motor type, spool-up acceleration, PWM frequency, beacon delay, and an adjustable BEC (this is only available for the 150A ESC). Most of these revisions are self-explanatory but the "Beacon Delay" does require an explanation. The "Beacon Delay" is quite a unique function that will cause the ESC to start "beeping" after a predetermined delay of not using the throttle stick, this delay can be set from between 1 and 10mins using this program card. The loud beeping noise is perfect for finding your model if it gets lost in high grass, standing crops, or in the bush, etc. Please note that you can use this programming card to program earlier versions of the Plush 32 series but only ESCs with the Rev1.1.0 firmware will show the revised functions.

Description: More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. For pilots, it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. By improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

ToolkitRC M6D Dual 1~6S 15A 250W DC Balance Charger/Discharger
Description: The ToolkitRC M6D is a versatile dual battery charger that integrates functions such as charging, synchronous charging, discharging, cycling, and smart consumer-grade drone battery charging, it also has a multilingual user interface. The M6D is a DC unit only, so requires an input voltage of 7~28V DC, this makes it perfect for charging at the flying field, race track, or boating lake. For use in the workshop, it can be connected to a mains power supply that can supply the correct DC voltage, and a current of 30A.The M6DAC is capable of charging two batteries at up to 250W each, or, if both channels are used, in the synchronous mode for one battery pack, then it can charge the pack at up to a very impressive 500W. A wide variety of different chemistry batteries can also be charged on the M6D, these include, LiPo, LiHV, LiFe, and Li-ion @ 1~6S, NiMh @ 1~16S, and Pb @ 1~10S.The M6D is simple and straightforward to use, it has an easy-to-read, wide-angle, back-lit, IPS 2.4"x320x240 pixel full-color LCD screen, simple to use metal, menu scrolling/enter wheel, and a ch/exit button. Ports include an XT60 DC input socket, and outputs include 2 x XT60 charging ports, 2 x 2~6S balance ports, a temperature sensor port, and a USB output/upgrade port. When required, the powerful, intelligent, high-flow cooling fan cuts in at half speed when internal temperatures of the charger exceed 45°C, this will then switch to full power when temperatures exceed 53°C.The ToolkitRC M6D dual battery balance charger/discharger is a must for every modeler due to its compact size, incredible charging power, and its easy-to-use, intuitive programming menus.

Title: RADIOMASTER TX16S MKII ELRS 16ch FCC 2.4GHz RC Transmitter w/V4.0 Hall Gimbals
Description: The best just got better, the RADIOMASTER TX16S MKII is the ultimate open-source radio. It is still a high-end, low-cost, OpenTx radio that has many great features, and this version includes the powerful long-range ELRS protocol. With the MKII you get many new features, these include, improved internal circuitry, V4.0 Hall sensor gimbals for improved centering, improved ergonomics, redesigned battery cover, and improved knobs and sliders that are smoother with a better center ident.The TX16S MKII transmitter supports EdgeTX and OpenTX open source firmware which is fully supported by the OpenTX development team. RADIOMASTER works closely with the EdgeTX team to develop and optimize the user experience and will continue to ensure that the concept and standards are carried forward into the future. The TX16S MKII is available in either an FCC version or a European LBT version, please check the specifications below for the supported protocol.There is a module slot in the back of the transmitter which will accept the popular JR/FrSky/TBS Crossfire type of module which means you can be up and running almost instantly with your favorite protocols. There is no need to remove the external module if you have one plugged in as the TX16S can be switched easily between the internal RF and the external RF. The transmitter is also Mode selectable so it can be either Mode 1 or Mode 2, this does, however, require the back being removed to move some mechanical components from one stick unit to the other.The supplied battery tray will accept either 2 x 3.7V 18650 Lithium-Ion batteries or 2 x 3.7V LiPo batteries. The large battery compartment (97x52x25mm) also has room for a 2S LiPo pack of your choice. A nice feature of this radio is that the batteries can stay in the compartment and be charged via the USB-C charging port. Another improvement of the MKII is that it now allows for charge rates of up to 2.2A. Other ports include a new 3.5mm audio jack, 3.5mm TRS trainer socket, a USB data port, SD card slot, and 2 UART ports to expand the capabilities of the radio.Overall this improved MKII version is an easy-to-use, OpenTx transmitter with the ELRS protocol that has loads of features, and many improvements over earlier versions.

Title: Turnigy Plush-32 20A (2~4S) Brushless Speed Controller w/BEC (Rev1.1.0)
Description: The Turnigy Plush-32 brushless ESC comes with a 32-bit ARM controller which offers higher resolution, makes it quicker, smoother, and more responsive to your throttle inputs. As you would expect, all the Turnigy Plush-32 are manufactured to the same high-quality standards that you have come to expect with all the Turnigy Plush ESCs.Now with the updated Rev1.1.0 firmware, these speed controllers offer a few more programming options over previous models. These include motor type, spool-up acceleration, PWM frequency, beacon delay, and an adjustable BEC (this is only available on the 150A). Most of these revisions are self-explanatory but the "Beacon Delay" does require an explanation. The "Beacon Delay" is quite a unique function that will cause the ESC to start "beeping" after a predetermined delay of not using the throttle stick, this can be set via the program card. The loud beeping noise is perfect for finding your model if it gets lost in high grass, standing crops, or in the bush, etc. Please note that you can use your existing Plush 32 programming card but you will not be able to access the revised functions unless you purchase the new Rev1.1.0 programming card.Programming your Plush 32 ESC is made very simple if you use the Plush 32 programming card. No more listening to the beeps, and guessing when to move your throttle, the programming card changes settings with the press of a button. Easy-to-read LEDs let you know exactly how your ESC is being programmed and set. So don’t forget to include a programming card when purchasing your ESC, see related products.

Title: RADIOMASTER MT12 ELRS FCC Surface Transmitter w/ER3C-i Receiver
Description: The RADIOMASTER MT12 is a pioneering open-source surface radio, and the first surface radio officially supported by the EdgeTX and ExpressLRS multi-module project. The MT12 is available as either an ELRS or 4-in-1 multi-module version (see specs) and boasts 10 physical inputs, and the capability to handle either 16 or 32 channels (4-in-1 version only). The ELRS (ExpressLRS) version is designed to provide a reliable long-range, ultra-fast response, super low latency, and high refresh rates. ELRS is a revolutionary open-source protocol taking the R/C industry by storm. Each version is also available in either an FCC version or a European LBT version, please check the specifications below for the supported protocol.The EdgeTX system is preinstalled and the MT12 has cutting-edge software fit for its class-leading hardware. RADIOMASTER works closely with the EdgeTX team to develop new features and optimize the user experience for surface models. RADIOMASTER will also continue to contribute and support projects like EdgeTX, ensuring the concepts of open standards are carried forward, for more information, please visit https://edgetx.org/Just a few of the features of the MT12 include a standardized button layout and CNC menu wheel, adjustable throttle trigger to suit your driving style, adjustable wheel tension, Hall sensors for accurate inputs and precise centering, 5 trim buttons, and an external NANO module. Included with the transmitter is an ER3C-i receiver that also utilizes the revolutionary ExpressLRS system, for high reliability, ultra-fast response speeds, and an ultra-long receiving range. It can drive up to 3 servos, has built-in receiver voltage telemetry, and a built-in, highly sensitive ceramic antenna.The MT12 is primed for a wide array of surface models, from cars and trucks to boats and much more. Featuring extensive customizability and a versatile operating system, the MT12 stands out as a highly configurable surface radio, prepared to excel in virtually any scenario.

Title: XK (RTF) K110S 6ch Brushless CP Micro 3D Helicopter w/Switchable 3/6-Axis Gyro & Hover Mode
Description: The XK K110S CP micro helicopter with collective pitch and a brushless motor is the perfect choice for those pilots who want to progress on the exciting journey of learning to fly RC helicopters. Being an upgraded version of the popular K110, the K110S is very capable of performing advanced aerobatics and 3D flight, but it is also equally at home flying as a stable intermediate training platform. The XK K110S is stabilized using a state-of-the-art gyro system that has the ability to be switched from 6-axis for super stable flight, to 3-axis for aerobatic and wild 3D flight. A very handy feature when you have the 6-axis gyro selected is "Hover Mode", at the flick of a switch on the transmitter the K110S will sit in a stable hover without any inputs from you on the control sticks.Included in the box is everything you need to get flying, a 2.4Ghz 6ch transmitter with a large LCD screen for programming different settings, a 3.7V 450mAh 25C LiPo battery, and a USB charging system that is capable of charging 2 batteries simultaneously. The transmitter has the ability to be easily switched to operate as either Mode 1 or Mode 2, these modes give you the choice of which control functions are on which control sticks. Also included are some tools, a spare set of main rotor blades, and a spare tail blade, plus an informative instruction manual.Another quite unique feature for a small ready-to-fly helicopter is that it can be flown if you wish using a Futaba S-FHSS radio system. This will appeal to experienced pilots who would like to use their own Futaba computer radio to fly the XK K110S. Power to the main rotors is supplied by a powerful 1106-11000KV brushless motor, and the tail by an efficient and reliable 0176 hollow-cup motor. This coupled with the K110S being manufactured to the highest of standards, with the highest quality components for strength, reliability, and crash resistance, makes this a must-have heli for the intermediate to experienced RC pilot.

Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!Lithium Polymer batteries are used in many RC hobby industries. Over the last few years, Lipo batteries have become the most popular battery choice for anyone looking for a longer run time and higher power.Lipo batteries weigh less and can be made into almost any size or shape. Lipo batteries have higher capacities, hold more power and have a higher discharge rate, meaning they pack more punch. For the safe use and storage of Lipo batteries, you need to follow the rules and treat the batteries with the respect they deserve.Suited to the following models:5S x 2:MIKADO LOGO600/600SE, Century Swift 620SE, Synergy E9, HIROBO Eagle3 EPThe nano-core technology in lithium-ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high-rate discharge decreases greatly.

Included with the transmitter is an ER3C-i receiver that also utilizes the revolutionary ExpressLRS system, for high reliability, ultra-fast response speeds, and an ultra-long receiving range. It can drive up to 3 servos, has built-in receiver voltage telemetry, and a built-in, highly sensitive ceramic antenna.The MT12 is primed for a wide array of surface models, from cars and trucks to boats and much more. Featuring extensive customizability and a versatile operating system, the MT12 stands out as a highly configurable surface radio, prepared to excel in virtually any scenario.

Description: If you’re craving speed, the EFXtra is where it’s at, with out-of-the-box performance in excess of 100mph+. Title: XK (RTF) K110S 6ch Brushless CP Micro 3D Helicopter w/Switchable 3/6-Axis Gyro & Hover Mode
Description: The XK K110S CP micro helicopter with collective pitch and a brushless motor is the perfect choice for those pilots who want to progress on the exciting journey of learning to fly RC helicopters. Being an upgraded version of the popular K110, the K110S is very capable of performing advanced aerobatics and 3D flight, but it is also equally at home flying as a stable intermediate training platform. The XK K110S is stabilized using a state-of-the-art gyro system that has the ability to be switched from 6-axis for super stable flight, to 3-axis for aerobatic and wild 3D flight. A very handy feature when you have the 6-axis gyro selected is "Hover Mode", at the flick of a switch on the transmitter the K110S will sit in a stable hover without any inputs from you on the control sticks.Included in the box is everything you need to get flying, a 2.4Ghz 6ch transmitter with a large LCD screen for programming different settings, a 3.7V 450mAh 25C LiPo battery, and a USB charging system that is capable of charging 2 batteries simultaneously. The transmitter has the ability to be easily switched to operate as either Mode 1 or Mode 2, these modes give you the choice of which control functions are on which control sticks. Also included are some tools, a spare set of main rotor blades, and a spare tail blade, plus an informative instruction manual.Another quite unique feature for a small ready-to-fly helicopter is that it can be flown if you wish using a Futaba S-FHSS radio system. This will appeal to experienced pilots who would like to use their own Futaba computer radio to fly the XK K110S. Power to the main rotors is supplied by a powerful 1106-11000KV brushless motor, and the tail by an efficient and reliable 0176 hollow-cup motor. This coupled with the K110S being manufactured to the highest of standards, with the highest quality components for strength, reliability, and crash resistance, makes this a must-have heli for the intermediate to experienced RC pilot.

Title: Turnigy nano-tech 2700mah 4S 65~130C Lipo Pack w/XT-60
Description: More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. Utilising an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and a higher discharge rates than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) batteries.For those that love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves and excellent performance. For pilots it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!Lithium Polymer batteries are used in many RC hobby industries. Over the last few years, Lipo batteries have become the most popular battery choice for anyone looking for a longer run time and higher power.Lipo batteries weigh less and can be made into almost any size or shape. Lipo batteries have higher capacities, hold more power and have a higher discharge rate, meaning they pack more punch. For safe use and storage of Lipo batteries, you need to follow the rules and treat the batteries with the respect they deserve.Spec.Capacity:2700mAhVoltage:4S1P / 4 Cell / 14.8VDischarge:65C Constant / 130C BurstWeight:332g (including wire, plug & case)Dimensions:134 x 44 x 27mmBalance Plug:JST-XHDischarge Plug:XT-60Advantages over traditional Lipoly batteries;• Power density reaches 7.5 kw/kg.• Less Voltage sag during high rate discharge, giving more power under load.• Internal impedance can reach as low as 1.2mO compared to that of 3mO of a standard Lipoly.• Greater thermal control, pack usually doesn’t exceed 60degC• Swelling during heavy load doesn’t exceed 5%, compared to 15% of a normal Lipoly.• Higher capacity during heavy discharge. More than 90% at 100% C rate.• Fast charge capable, up to 15C on some batteries.• Longer Cycle Life, almost double that of standard lipoly technology.The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

Title: ToolkitRC Q4AC (US Plug) 1~4S 5A 200W AC/DC Quad Balance Charger/Discharger
Description: The ToolkitRC Q4AC is a 4-channel (Quad) smart charger that will independently charge/discharge 4 batteries at the same time. The Q4AC has a built-in 100W power supply that allows it to be powered from a 100~240V AC mains power source. It also has the ability to operate on a 10~18V DC power supply which is perfect for charging at the flying field, race track, or boating lake.Navigation and programming of the Q4AC 4 menu channels are made very easy with the wide-angle, back-lit, IPS 3.5"x480x320 resolution full-color LCD screen, and metal scrolling wheel. A wide variety of different chemistry batteries can be charged, these include, LiPo, LiHV, LiFe, Li-ion, and LTO (Lithium-Titanium-Oxide) @ 1~4S, NiMh @ 1~10S, and Pb @ 1~8S. With a DC power input the charger operates as 4 independent 50W channels, this gives a combined total output of 200W. With an AC power input, the charge power is reduced to 25W per channel, this gives a maximum for the charger of 100W. However, 2 channels can be combined when using AC to produce 50W or charging power.Because each channel is completely independent, different parameters can be set for each of the 4 channels, this includes charging or discharging different chemistry batteries. Inputs include an AC mains socket, a DC XT60 socket, and a micro USB port for updating the firmware, outputs include 4 x XT60 charging ports, and 4 x 2~4S balance ports. When required, the powerful, intelligent, high-flow cooling fan cuts in at half speed when internal temperatures of the charger exceed 42°C, this will then switch to full power when temperatures exceed 50°C.The ToolkitRC MQ4AC quad balance charger/discharger is a must for every modeler's workshop due to its versatility of being able to charge, or discharge 4 batteries simultaneously, and independently, its ability to run from AC and DC power sources, and its easy-to-use, intuitive programming menus.

Title: Aerostar 80A RVS G2 32bit (2~6S) Electronic Speed Controller w/Reverse Function & 8A 5~6V SBEC
Description: The Aerostar RVS G2 next-generation range of brushless speed controllers moves up a notch from the ground-breaking original Aerostar RVS ESCs. They are more compact, lighter, and process faster due to high-performance 32bit technology, have improved functionality and programmable features, and an upgraded, high-amp SBEC system. New generation MOSFETs ensure that the ESC stays within operating temperatures, and can also safely handle the peak current draw specified. Our RVS (reverse function system) is now instantaneous, with no need for the motor to stop turning, this makes it perfect for EDF braking (reverse thrust), and waterplanes for taxiing, etc. If you don't require the reverse function, simply do not connect the second lead to your receiver, it will then operate as a standard ESC.The Aerostar RVS G2 brushless reversing speed controllers have been designed for a range of fixed-wing applications including as mentioned above, EDF braking (reverse thrust), floatplane/flying boat operations, and with the soft-start function, geared motors using large standard or folding propellers. Another feature of the G2 range of ESC is the addition of HEF (Higher-Efficiency Function) technology. The HEF circuitry allows for better heat dissipation, and lower energy loss when used with certain applications, this function when selected is very similar to "Active Freewheeling". When set to "Off" (the factory default) it's perfect for low to medium KV outrunner motors, when set to "On", it's perfect for high KV outrunners, and inrunners such as those used in EDFs or direct drive racing models.Features that have been retained from the original version are the super smooth start-up, linear throttle response, and multiple protection features. These protections include start-up (prevents motor accidentally starting when powering up), low-voltage cut-off, phase loss, and signal loss, to fully protect the components of your ESC. Programming the many functions of the Aerostar RVS G2 ESC is very simple using either your transmitter or the optional LCD programming card.Installation is very straightforward as these speed controllers come "Plug N Play", no soldering is required as they are supplied pre-fitted with an XT90 connector for the battery, and 4mm gold connectors for the motor.

Well not only do Graphene batteries go harder for longer but they're unlike anything you have seen or used before.Turnigy Graphene packs utilize carbon in the battery structure to form a single layer of graphene just 0.335nm thick, making that type of battery substrate the thinnest known to mankind. Title: SonicModell (PNF) AR Wing PRO "White Falcon" EPP 1000mm
Description: The SonicModell AR Wing PRO "White Falcon" is a special, all-white version of the popular standard AR Wing PRO. It is still a tough, dynamic, efficient, lifting-body flying wing that delivers an impressive performance with style. The White Falcon features detachable wings, so there is no glue required, and the elevon servo connections are made automatically, which means the wings can be easily removed for transport. Other features are a large battery/flight controller bay, a nose camera bay for FPV flying that suits DJI and other cameras, and numerous compartments for the FPV transmitter (plenty of room for long-range systems) and your RC receiver, etc. These compartments have aerodynamically designed NACA air cooling systems to keep everything including your FPV gear nice and cool.The aerodynamic design allows for a highly agile, responsive, and precise flying model that gives a sharp reaction to your control inputs. The White Falcon is no slouch in the performance department either, with its included power system it can reach speeds of up to 130km/h. This is very impressive, but its wide speed range means that it is equally happy flying around very slowly as well.Supplied as "Plug-N-Fly", the White Falcon is equipped with a powerful 2216-1400KV brushless motor driving a 2-blade 8x5 propeller, this is matched to a 40A ESC with 5V 3A BEC, and the supplied 9g analog servos are metal geared. The airframe is nicely molded in tough white EPP foam, complete with molded C of G dimples, and for enhanced stability and crash resistance, there is a strong carbon-fiber wing spar. The bottom of the White Falcon is completely flat with stick-on teflon skids, there is nothing really to catch on the ground when landing (apart from the surface control horns) to cause damage, even the servo horns are recessed. The control surfaces themselves come molded to the wing itself with a foam hinge, but CA hinges are also provided as an option. The control surface side of things is completed with a highly accurate, no-slop ball link system.The SonicModell AR Wing PRO "White Falcon" offers great performance, stacks of room for all your equipment, has an impressive payload of around 900g, is very easy to assemble, and is the perfect package for FPV and pure fun flying.

Title: RADIOMASTER RP2 V2 FCC ExpressLRS 2.4GHz Nano Receiver
Description: The RadioMaster RP V2 series of receivers now have a built-in TCXO (Temperature-Compensated Xtal Oscillator). The TCXO ensures high stability and accuracy in frequency control and compensates for temperature variations. This results in consistent and reliable signal reception, even in extreme temperature conditions. It also reduces frequency drift over time, providing long-term frequency stability and preventing signal degradation. This provides a superior performance in demanding environments and enhances the flight experiences.The RP2 2.4GHz ELRS Nano receivers use the high-performance, revolutionary ExpressLRS open-source system. The Nano receivers were designed by the ExpressLRS development team, and feature the ESP8285 MCU and SX1280 RF chips. WiFi is built-in so that you can easily upgrade the firmware and configure the receiver using your PC or mobile phone. Other features of the RP2 V2 are improved solder pads and a super lightweight built-in ceramic antenna.Due to the low-latency and high-refresh-rate RF module, this receiver is ideal for FPV racing or long-range flying. The RP2 Nano receiver is available in either an FCC or a European LBT version, please check the specifications below for the supported protocol.

Title: GOOSKY (RTF) Mode 2 Legend S2 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter (Blue/Green)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S2 is a game-changing, high-performance, innovative, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring you unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including a flybarless head, dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique one-piece concave CNC bracket for the swashplate actuator system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the GOOSKY R&D team in producing a tough, exciting-to-fly, low-maintenance, high-performance helicopter, that is suitable for low-time and experienced pilots alike.This RTF (Ready-to-Fly) version of the Legend S2 is not only supplied with metal-geared servos, flight controller, and battery but a dedicated, simple-to-use GOOSKY T8 transmitter as well. This transmitter is squarely aimed at the novice pilot, with no complicated computer programming, basically just switch it on and fly, but it is also perfect for the more experienced pilot who just wants to get flying quickly and easily. Out of the box, the 2 factory set defaults allow for either a sedate, quiet flying machine on the fully stabilized setting, or flick the Tx flight mode switch into the advanced setting to unleash a wild and exciting 3D aerobatic machine. The transmitter is Mode 2, meaning that the left/right, and fore/aft cyclic are on the right stick, and throttle/tail rotor are on the left stick. The T8 also includes its own 3.7V 18650 2800mAh battery which is easily charged via the Type-C USB port in the side of the transmitter.The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precise control of the two flight modes as mentioned above. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler. The T8 transmitter uses the popular S-FHSS protocol which the GTS system is set up for, however, it can also be matched to a DSMX system if you wish by adding a DSMX-compatible satellite receiver.Other features include a quick-release tail rotor blade system, CNC machined metal parts for reinforcement of the frame, fixed length pushrods for accurate set-up, tough one-piece landing gear, high-strength alloy tail boom, and a unique tail boom holder design to help minimize damage in a crash.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to fly, you just need to charge the battery and away you go. If you need to change the default settings, then this is quick and simple via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S2 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning, tough, and well-engineered helicopter.

Title: Aerostar 80A RVS G2 32bit (2~6S) Electronic Speed Controller w/Reverse Function & 8A 5~6V SBEC
Description: The Aerostar RVS G2 next-generation range of brushless speed controllers moves up a notch from the ground-breaking original Aerostar RVS ESCs. They are more compact, lighter, and process faster due to high-performance 32bit technology, have improved functionality and programmable features, and an upgraded, high-amp SBEC system. New generation MOSFETs ensure that the ESC stays within operating temperatures, and can also safely handle the peak current draw specified. Our RVS (reverse function system) is now instantaneous, with no need for the motor to stop turning, this makes it perfect for EDF braking (reverse thrust), and waterplanes for taxiing, etc. If you don't require the reverse function, simply do not connect the second lead to your receiver, it will then operate as a standard ESC.The Aerostar RVS G2 brushless reversing speed controllers have been designed for a range of fixed-wing applications including as mentioned above, EDF braking (reverse thrust), floatplane/flying boat operations, and with the soft-start function, geared motors using large standard or folding propellers. Another feature of the G2 range of ESC is the addition of HEF (Higher-Efficiency Function) technology. The HEF circuitry allows for better heat dissipation, and lower energy loss when used with certain applications, this function when selected is very similar to "Active Freewheeling". When set to "Off" (the factory default) it's perfect for low to medium KV outrunner motors, when set to "On", it's perfect for high KV outrunners, and inrunners such as those used in EDFs or direct drive racing models.Features that have been retained from the original version are the super smooth start-up, linear throttle response, and multiple protection features. These protections include start-up (prevents motor accidentally starting when powering up), low-voltage cut-off, phase loss, and signal loss, to fully protect the components of your ESC. Programming the many functions of the Aerostar RVS G2 ESC is very simple using either your transmitter or the optional LCD programming card.Installation is very straightforward as these speed controllers come "Plug N Play", no soldering is required as they are supplied pre-fitted with an XT90 connector for the battery, and 4mm gold connectors for the motor.

Title: Turnigy nano-tech 1200mAh 3S 25-50C Lipo AIRSOFT Pack
Description: Get an unfair advantage with Turnigy Nano-tech Airsoft Packs!On the battlefeild, no one wants to compromise on fire power! That's why the legendary Turnigy nano-tech batteries are available as a drop-in replacement pack for an upgrade in firepower.Turnigy Nano-tech Airsoft batteries are superior to the standard NiMH batteries offering faster charge rates and higher voltages. In short, the first thing your opponent will notice is sustained rapid fire pinning him down.It's clear why Turnigy Nano-techs are the go to pack for anyone who is serious about Airsoft.The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels.This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.

Description: We pulled out the defibrillator and shocked some serious life in to the Dead Cat conversion! Title: Turnigy Evolution Mode 1 PRO Digital AFHDS 2A Radio Control System (Black) w/TGY-iA6C Receiver
Description: After the huge success of the Turnigy Evolution, the Evolution PRO is designed with the drone flier in mind and is still amazingly compact for easy backpack transportation.There are many new features and updates to make the Evolution PRO the best radio around. Starting with a repositioned on/off switch and a new lanyard attachment point for easier use. There are now stiffer springs to help the sticks and a repositioned screen so that people that are “pinchers” have better control of the sticks plus the user now has access to stick calibration. A momentary button has been added which is great to use as pre-arm on quads. For those that had trouble hearing the buzzer the sound has been made louder and there is haptic feedback. Now you can store twenty different models (instead of five) for easier swapping of models. Firmware has also been updated from the Evolution.The ergonomically designed case makes for easy use of all controls. The switches are all positioned for comfort and the adjustable length sticks can be tailored to your own requirements. Speaking of sticks, the high quality, ball bearing gimbals are clear and have color changing, programmable LEDs that can change color with the use of the sticks. Two 3-position switches on the back can easily be set-up to change the flight modes. A large monochrome backlit LCD Touch screen makes it easy to program and change the settings in both daylight and night-time.The Evolution PRO uses the solid and reliable 8 channel 2.4GHz Automatic Frequency Hopping Digital System (AFHDS 2A) spread spectrum technology, making it compatible with the iA6, iA6B, iA6C, iA10B range of receivers. The system is supplied with the Turnigy TGY-iA6C Receiver for SBUS/IBUS and CPPM support. Twin omnidirectional high gain antennas are built into the outer case to provide an even more secure radio link and to protect them from damage.Each transmitter hops between 16 channels in order to reduce interference from other transmitters. The transmitter and receiver have their own unique ID to prevent other RC systems from accidentally connecting to or interfering with the Evolution PRO. There is even a mini USB port for easy charging via a power bank (power pack) or phone charger / USB charger / PC. This can also be used for updates (via PC) or to use the Evolution PRO transmitter as a controller for your favorite RC simulator programs. Title: Turnigy nano-tech 2250mah 4S 65~130C Lipo Pack
Description: More than just a fancy name. TURNIGY nano-tech Lipoly batteries were designed from the ground up with serious performance in mind. Utilising an advanced LiCo nano-technology substrate that allows electrons to pass more freely from anode to cathode with less internal impedance. In short; less voltage sag and a higher discharge rates than a similar density lithium polymer (non nano-tech) batteries.For those that love graphs, it means higher voltage under load, straighter discharge curves and excellent performance. For pilots it spells stronger throttle punches and unreal straight-up performance. Excellent news for 3D pilots!Unfortunately with other big brands; numbers, ratings and graphs can be fudged. Rest assured, TURNIGY nano-techs are the real deal, delivering unparalleled performance!The nano-core technology in lithium ion batteries is the application of nanometer conductive additives. The nanometer conductive additives form ultra-strong electron-conducting networks in the electrodes which can increase electronic conductivity.These additives create the ability for imbibition in the carrier liquid to supply more ion channels. This improves the ability of ion transmission and ion diffusion. Through improving electronic conductivity and ion transmission, the impedance is reduced and the polarization of high rate discharge decreases greatly.
advantages: ['• Power density reaches 7.5 kw/kg.', '• Less Voltage sag during high rate discharge, giving more power under load.', '• Internal impedance can reach as low as 1.2mO compared to that of 3mO of a standard Lipoly.', '• Greater thermal control, pack usually doesn’t exceed 60degC', '• Swelling during heavy load doesn’t exceed 5%, compared to 15% of a normal Lipoly.', '• Higher capacity during heavy discharge. More than 90% at 100% C rate.', '• Fast charge capable, up to 15C on some batteries.', '• Longer Cycle Life, almost double that of standard lipoly technology.']

Title: RADIOMASTER BOXER MAX (Gold) ELRS FCC M2 16ch 2.4GHz RC Transmitter w/Open-Source EdgeTX Firmware
Description: The RADIOMASTER BOXER MAX radio has been created to be the best radio in its class without compromising anything. It is supplied with the EdgeTX operating system, and the ExpressLRS RF system pre-installed (FCC or LBT). There is also an external JR-style module compartment so that you can use all your favorite modules and protocols.The BOXER MAX has to be one of the coolest-looking transmitters on the market. It comes with a simulated carbon-fiber finish as standard and is available with 3 options for the color of the gimbals, and the CNC machined switches, buttons, and roller, etc. These options are red, gold, and black, this one being the stylish gold version.The amount of features is too numerous to list, but here is a small selection of the many incredible features of the BOXER MAX. Super-smooth AG01 hall sensor gimbals, adjustable length CNC metal folding stand, comfortable leather grips, compact ergonomic design, oversized battery compartment for large battery packs (batteries not supplied), adjustable, and removable "T" shape antenna, versatile 6-position switch for flight mode access, and so much more. Also included is a high-density, shock-proof padded storage and carry case. This is perfect for keeping your treasured transmitter safe whilst being stored or traveling.As mentioned above, the RADIOMASTER BOXER MAX has the cutting-edge EDGETX software pre-installed. This open-source firmware is highly customizable to allow users to configure their transmitters through the supplied USB-C data port to adjust the settings for their individual preferences and specific needs. EdgeTX supports a wide range of RC protocols and is a versatile and powerful tool which makes it extremely popular with the RC community. RADIOMASTER works closely with the EdgeTX team to develop and optimize the user experience and will continue to ensure that the concept and standards are carried forward into the future. The programming of the transmitter is a very simple affair as well, using a combination of the system/page buttons, and the menu scrolling wheel.Overall this is an easy-to-use, flexible, compact, open-source transmitter that is ergonomically designed, making it comfortable to hold, and it has a string of high-quality features that puts it in a class of its own.

Title: GOOSKY (RTF) Mode 2 Legend S1 Dual Brushless High-Performance Aerobatic Helicopter (White)
Description: The GOOSKY Legend S1 is a small, game-changing, high-performance, aerobatic helicopter that incorporates all the latest in cutting-edge design and technology to bring unmatched flying fun and excitement. It boasts a whole host of features including dual direct drive powerful brushless motors (one main, one tail), a compact GTS control system with Bluetooth mobile phone APP for parameter adjustments, a unique "cage body" metal geared servo system, highly efficient low noise rotor blades, and quick and easy battery changing. Every detail reflects the ingenuity of the designers in producing a tough, easy-to-fly, maintenance-free, high-performance helicopter suitable for entry-level and experienced pilots alike.This RTF (Ready-to-Fly) version of the Legend S1 is supplied not only with the servos, flight controller, 2 batteries, and charger, but a dedicated, simple-to-use GOOSKY T8 transmitter as well. This transmitter is squarely aimed at the beginner, no complicated computer programming, basically just switch on and fly, but it is also perfect for the more experienced pilot who just wants to get flying quickly and easily. The transmitter is Mode 2, meaning that the left/right, and fore/aft cyclic are on the right stick, and throttle/tail rotor are on the left stick. The T8 also includes its own 3.7V 18650 2800mAh battery which is easily charged via the Type-C USB port in the side of the transmitter. The included GTS flight controller system utilizes new frame algorithmic technology for precision control with two flight modes. Flight mode 1 (switchable from the Tx) is self-stabilization that offers amazing stability for the beginner, and flight mode 2 allows for high-performance aerobatics and full 3D flight. The parameters of this system such as gyro settings, control throws, pitch, and head speeds are fully adjustable via the GOOSKY mobile phone APP and the supplied Bluetooth module, what could be simpler.This incredible helicopter is a must-have for all RC pilots, it comes out of the box ready to fly, you just need to charge one of the batteries and away you go. If you need to change the default settings, then this is quick and simple via the GOOSKY APP. The most important thing to remember is, the GOOSKY Legend S1 is exciting, and great fun to fly, so get out there and enjoy this stunning little helicopter.

Title: RADIOMASTER BOXER (Transparent) ELRS FCC 16ch 2.4GHz RC Transmitter w/Open-Source EdgeTX Firmware
Description: The RADIOMASTER BOXER radio has been created to be the best radio in its class without compromising anything. This version is supplied with the EdgeTX operating system pre-installed (FCC or LBT, see specs), and the long-range ELRS protocol. There is also an external JR-style module compartment so that you can use all your favorite modules and protocols.The popular Boxer radio is now available in a Transparent Edition, an electrifying fusion of style and performance that is sure to set the RC community ablaze! Unleash the perfect balance of sleek design and high durability, all wrapped up in a premium transparent package. Prepare to be mesmerized with the bonus White LED kit included allowing you to customize the look of your radio even further. Included with this edition is a bonus neck strap to complete the set with style and comfort.The amount of features is too numerous to list, but here is a small selection of the many incredible features of the BOXER radio. Super-smooth AG01 hall sensor gimbals, adjustable length CNC metal folding stand, compact ergonomic design, oversized battery compartment for large battery packs (batteries not supplied), adjustable, and removable "T" shape antenna, versatile 6-position switch for flight mode access, and so much more. Also included is a high-density, shock-proof padded storage and carry case. This is perfect for keeping your treasured transmitter safe whilst being stored or traveling.As mentioned above, the RADIOMASTER BOXER has the cutting-edge EDGETX software pre-installed. This open-source firmware is highly customizable to allow users to configure their transmitters through the supplied USB-C data port to adjust the settings for their individual preferences and specific needs. EdgeTX supports a wide range of RC protocols and is a versatile and powerful tool which makes it extremely popular with the RC community. RADIOMASTER works closely with the EdgeTX team to develop and optimize the user experience and will continue to ensure that the concept and standards are carried forward into the future. The programming of the transmitter is a very simple affair as well, using a combination of the system/page buttons, and the menu scrolling wheel.Overall this is an easy-to-use, flexible, compact, open-source transmitter that is ergonomically designed, making it comfortable to hold, and it has a string of high-quality features that puts it in a class of its own.
